WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:31.000 --> 04:34.003
[ Girl Narrating ]
YOUR WHOLE LIFE CAN CHANGE
IN A SECOND,

04:34.003 --> 04:36.505
AND YOU NEVER EVEN KNOW
WHEN IT'S COMING.

04:38.007 --> 04:41.010
BEFORE, YOU THINK YOU KNOW
WHAT KIND OF WORLD THIS IS.

04:42.011 --> 04:45.514
AND AFTER,
EVERYTHING IS DIFFERENT FOR YOU.

04:48.017 --> 04:50.518
NOT BAD, MAYBE,
NOT ALWAYS...

04:51.520 --> 04:55.024
BUT DIFFERENT... FOREVER.

04:55.024 --> 04:58.026
???? [ Piano Continues ]

04:58.026 --> 05:01.030
[ Girl ]
I DIDN'T USED TO KNOW THAT...

05:01.030 --> 05:04.033
'TIL THE DAY IT HAPPENED
TO MY FAMILY.

05:04.033 --> 05:07.036
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THERE COULD BE
SUCH A THING AS "AFTER."

05:09.038 --> 05:13.541
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT, FOR US,
"BEFORE" WAS ALREADY OVER.

05:22.551 --> 05:25.054
[ Hits Wrong Note ]

05:36.064 --> 05:41.570
???? [ "Chopsticks"
Drowns Out Classical ]

05:44.072 --> 05:47.076
[ Both Laugh ]

05:49.078 --> 05:50.829
[ Giggling ]

05:52.831 --> 05:54.833
T.J., THIS WON'T HURT.
I PROMISE.

05:54.833 --> 05:56.835
THIS IS MY SPECIAL
BOO-BOO LIGHT.

05:56.835 --> 06:00.839
IN FACT, IT'S MAGIC.
DID YOU EVER SEE A MAGIC
BOO-BOO LIGHT BEFORE?

06:02.841 --> 06:05.844
[ Woman ]
HE HAD NO BUSINESS
BEING ON HIS BROTHER'S SLED.

06:05.844 --> 06:08.347
DARN THING'S
BIGGER THAN HE IS.
YOU'RE NEEDED DOWNSTAIRS.

06:08.347 --> 06:10.349
[ People Murmuring ]

06:10.349 --> 06:13.852
T.J.'S A LUCKY BOY,
MRS. FOLEY, BUT I'D
KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.

06:13.852 --> 06:15.854
IF HE COMPLAINS
OF NAUSEA OR DIZZINESS,

06:16.355 --> 06:19.858
OR EVEN IF HE JUST SEEMS
DROWSIER THAN NORMAL,
GIVE ME A CALL, OKAY?

06:19.858 --> 06:22.861
THAT'S NOT MAGIC.
THAT'S JUST A FLASHLIGHT.

06:23.362 --> 06:25.864
OH, YEAH?
HERE. BLOW.

06:27.366 --> 06:29.367
SEE?
[ Giggles ]

06:29.367 --> 06:31.370
SEE YOU LATER.

06:42.381 --> 06:44.882
SHE'S GONE, TRYGVE.
NO, DAMN IT.
THERE'S STILL A CHANCE.

06:44.882 --> 06:46.885
[ Trygve ]
GIVE ME THAT.
[ Doctor ]
TRYGVE, SHE'S GONE.

06:46.885 --> 06:49.388
SHE WASN'T GONNA
MAKE IT ANYWAY.

06:50.389 --> 06:52.390
[ Man ]
WE DID OUR BEST.

06:52.390 --> 06:54.393
LET'S BREAK IT DOWN.

06:54.393 --> 06:56.395
WHAT HAPPENED?
[ Doctor ]
SOME BASTARD CLOBBERED HER...

06:56.395 --> 06:58.897
UP NEAR POOR FARM ROAD,
THEN LEFT HER THERE.

06:58.897 --> 07:01.400
SHE WAS LYING IN THE SNOW
BY THAT POND.

07:03.402 --> 07:05.404
DO WE KNOW WHO THIS IS?

07:05.404 --> 07:08.406
[ Trygve ]
MARTHA TAVERNER.

07:08.907 --> 07:10.909
MARTHA TAVERNER.
MM-HMM.

07:10.909 --> 07:13.912
OH. I'VE MET HER.

07:13.912 --> 07:17.416
I EVEN TREATED HER ONCE,
I THINK, WHEN YOU WERE ON
VACATION, TRYGVE. REMEMBER?

07:17.416 --> 07:19.418
YEAH.

07:25.424 --> 07:27.926
[ Trygve ]
HE'S STILL OUT THERE,
WHOEVER DID THIS.

07:28.427 --> 07:30.928
COULD BE ANYWHERE.

07:34.433 --> 07:37.902
[ Girl ]
HEY, DAD. "THREE OUNCES
GROUND CUMIN SEED"?

07:37.902 --> 07:40.905
MM-HMM.
YUCK!
WHAT'S CUMIN SEED?

07:41.406 --> 07:42.907
OH-HO-HO-HO.

07:43.408 --> 07:46.410
THAT IS ABSOLUTELY
THE MOST CRUCIAL,

07:46.410 --> 07:50.415
FANTASTIC,
TOP-SECRET INGREDIENT
IN MY ENTIRE CHILI.

07:50.415 --> 07:53.417
[ Door Slamming ]
[ Girl ]
HI, MOM!

07:53.417 --> 07:56.421
HI. JACOB!

07:59.424 --> 08:03.428
JAKE'S PARKING IS GETTING
SLOPPIER THAN EVER.

08:03.428 --> 08:07.932
MAN! HIS CAR
IS ALL OVER THE PLACE.

08:07.932 --> 08:12.437
BEN? I SWEAR I COULD HARDLY
EVEN GET MINE IN THE GARAGE.

08:12.437 --> 08:14.439
PARKING IT RIGHT WOULD FEEL
TOO MUCH LIKE WORK.

08:14.439 --> 08:16.940
MM.
[ Chuckles ]

08:18.943 --> 08:20.945
HI.

08:20.945 --> 08:23.448
LET ME HAVE SOME.

08:23.448 --> 08:25.950
HEY, YOU'RE TREMBLING.
MM.

08:26.451 --> 08:28.453
I'M JUST... COLD.
SIT DOWN.

08:28.453 --> 08:31.455
[ Girl ]
DAD, THIS STUFF'S FREAKING OUT!
IN A MINUTE.

08:31.955 --> 08:34.458
CAROLYN, WHAT--
[ Deep Sigh ]

08:34.458 --> 08:36.461
WE HAD AN EVENT
AT THE HOSPITAL TODAY.

08:36.461 --> 08:38.462
[ Doorbell Rings ]
"EVENT"?

08:38.962 --> 08:40.965
DAD, COME QUICK!

08:40.965 --> 08:43.467
[ Doorbell Rings ]
AHHH.

08:47.471 --> 08:49.474
FRAN!
DR. RYAN.

08:49.474 --> 08:53.978
[ Chuckling ]
YOU HAVEN'T CALLED ME "DOCTOR"
SINCE WE FIRST MOVED UP HERE.

08:57.482 --> 08:59.984
HI, MOM.
BEN.
HEY THERE, CHIEF.

08:59.984 --> 09:01.985
OUT OF UNIFORM TODAY.
WHAT'S UP?

09:01.985 --> 09:05.490
UH, SORRY TO BARGE IN
ON YOU LIKE THIS,
RIGHT HERE AT SUPPERTIME.

09:05.490 --> 09:08.493
- GET YOU SOMETHING, FRAN?
A BEER, IF YOU'RE NOT ON DUTY.
- NO, NO, BEN.

09:08.493 --> 09:10.494
THAT'S OKAY.
THANKS. UM--

09:12.497 --> 09:13.998
[ Sighs ]
IS JACOB AROUND?

09:14.499 --> 09:18.502
HE'S UP IN HIS ROOM, I GUESS,
WITH THOSE DAMN HEADPHONES ON.
YOU KNOW JACOB.

09:18.502 --> 09:20.505
YOU DIDN'T
SEE HIM COME IN?
I WAS IN THE STUDIO.

09:22.507 --> 09:25.509
DO YOU NEED HIM FOR SOMETHING?
YOU WANT US TO GET HIM, FRAN?
I'LL GO.

09:25.509 --> 09:27.512
YEAH, GO ON, HONEY.

09:29.013 --> 09:31.015
IS THERE
SOMETHING WRONG?

09:34.519 --> 09:37.522
[ Expelling Air ]
OKAY, UH--

09:38.022 --> 09:41.525
SOMETHING HAPPENED
OUT ON POOR FARM ROAD TODAY.
SOMETHING PRETTY BAD.

09:41.525 --> 09:44.529
A GIRL
GOT HERSELF KILLED.

09:44.529 --> 09:47.031
- I KNOW. I SAW HER.
- WHAT?

09:47.031 --> 09:49.032
WE HAD HER IN E.R.
BEYOND SAVING.

09:49.032 --> 09:51.536
I MEAN, IT WAS--
IT WAS AWFUL.

09:51.536 --> 09:54.038
GEEZ.
THAT'S WHAT I WAS GONNA
TELL YOU WHEN I CAME IN.

09:54.038 --> 09:56.039
GOD, I'M SORRY.
WHAT DOES THAT HAVE TO DO
WITH JACOB?

09:56.540 --> 09:58.042
OH, GOD,
I DON'T--

09:58.543 --> 10:02.046
I DON'T WANNA
HAVE TO TELL YOU THIS.
I REALLY DON'T.

10:02.547 --> 10:04.548
JACOB WAS SEEN
WITH THE GIRL.

10:04.548 --> 10:06.551
HE PICKED HER UP
FROM WORK.

10:06.551 --> 10:10.554
SHE WORKS DOWN
AT JACEY'S AFTER SCHOOL,
MAKING ICE CREAM CONES.

10:10.554 --> 10:14.058
HE CAME BY IN HIS CAR,
AND THEY WENT OFF TOGETHER,
LIKE THEY'D BEEN DOIN'.

10:14.058 --> 10:16.561
AS FAR AS WE KNOW,
RIGHT NOW,

10:17.061 --> 10:19.062
HE WAS THE LAST PERSON
WITH HER.

10:19.062 --> 10:22.066
ARE YOU SAYING JACOB
WAS DATING THAT GIRL,
MARTHA TAVERNER?

10:22.066 --> 10:24.569
NO, NO. WHAT HE'S--
WHAT HE'S SAYING IS HE'S--

10:24.569 --> 10:27.070
[ Chuckles ]
HE'S STANDING HERE
IN OUR KITCHEN...

10:27.070 --> 10:29.073
SAYING THAT HE THINKS
OUR SON WAS--

10:29.574 --> 10:32.076
OH, FOR CRYING
OUT LOUD, FRAN.
BEN, HEY, HEY.

10:32.577 --> 10:35.580
LET'S NOT JUMP THE GUN HERE.
I JUST NEED TO TALK TO HIM.
JACOB!

10:35.580 --> 10:38.583
JESUS CHR--

10:38.583 --> 10:40.585
HE'S NOT UP THERE.
I LOOKED ALL OVER.
WELL, THAT'S CRAZY.

10:40.585 --> 10:43.588
I-I-- HIS CAR'S
IN THE GARAGE.
I JUST SAW IT.

10:43.588 --> 10:46.090
YOU HAVE A SPARE
SET OF KEYS
FOR THE CAR?

10:46.090 --> 10:48.092
YEAH, I THINK THAT I DO.
DADDY.

10:48.593 --> 10:50.594
SOMETHING'S HAPPENED,
JUDITH, BUT THERE'S BEEN
A MISUNDERSTANDING.

10:50.594 --> 10:52.597
WE'LL EXPLAIN LATER, OKAY?
MM-HMM.

10:52.597 --> 10:55.600
OKAY, WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

10:55.600 --> 10:57.601
DO WHAT?
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

10:57.601 --> 11:01.105
YOU CAN'T GO SNOOPING AROUND
IN SOMEBODY ELSE'S CAR.
LEGALLY, THAT'S MY CAR.

11:01.105 --> 11:03.107
YOU DO NOT HAVE
A SEARCH WARRANT.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

11:03.608 --> 11:07.111
I'M SURE THERE'S SOME
VERY SIMPLE EXPLANATION
FOR ALL OF THIS.

11:07.111 --> 11:11.115
JACOB AND THE TAVERNER GIRL
MUST HAVE SEPARATED SOMEHOW
BEFORE THIS EVEN HAPPENED.

11:11.115 --> 11:13.617
YOU KNOW, MAYBE HE JUST
DROPPED HER OFF SOMEWHERE.

11:13.617 --> 11:17.121
MAYBE SHE GOT OUT
OF THE CAR AND WALKED AWAY.
THERE'S A THOUSAND DIFFERENT--

11:21.626 --> 11:23.127
FRAN, HOW DO WE KNOW
HE'S ALL RIGHT?

11:25.630 --> 11:31.135
MAYBE SOME MADMAN DID SOMETHING
TO BOTH OF THEM, AND MAYBE
JACOB'S HURT, OR HE'S KIDNAPPED.

11:32.136 --> 11:34.138
OH, MY GOD.

11:34.138 --> 11:37.642
CAROLINE, FOR HIS OWN SAKE,
THAT CAR MIGHT GIVE US
SOME ANSWERS.

11:39.644 --> 11:42.646
NO.
[ Gasps ]

11:42.646 --> 11:44.649
[ Sighs ]

11:44.649 --> 11:47.151
YOU'RE HIS PARENTS.
YOU WANNA PROTECT HIM.

11:47.151 --> 11:50.654
I GOT KIDS TOO,
BUT--

11:50.654 --> 11:54.158
BEN, IS THERE SOMETHING
THAT YOU KNOW THAT YOU'RE
NOT TELLIN' ME?

11:59.162 --> 12:01.165
HOW 'BOUT IT, JUDITH?
YOU KNOW ANYTHING--
HEY! HEY!

12:01.666 --> 12:04.168
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
OFF LIMITS! LEAVE HER
OUT OF THIS, OKAY?

12:04.669 --> 12:06.670
OKAY, PLEASE, PLEASE, BEN.
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I KNOW.

12:06.670 --> 12:08.673
IT'S JUST FRAN.
I KNOW
MY SON!

12:08.673 --> 12:11.676
HE'S JUST TRYING TO HELP US
FIND HIM, DARLIN'.
I DON'T WANT IT TO BE LIKE THIS.

12:11.676 --> 12:14.678
BUT IF I HAVE TO,
I WILL GO FIND JUDGE GRADY,
AND I WILL GET A SEARCH WARRANT.

12:14.678 --> 12:16.681
YEAH, YEAH.
YOU DO THAT!
AND I WILL BE
RIGHT BACK HERE.

12:16.681 --> 12:19.684
IT'S OKAY.
OKAY.

12:19.684 --> 12:23.688
SWEETIE, YOU LOOKED UPSTAIRS?
YOU'RE SURE?
YOU LOOKED EVERYPLACE?

12:31.195 --> 12:34.198
[ Car Engine Starts ]

12:34.198 --> 12:36.199
WE SHOULD HAVE LET HIM
LOOK IN THE CAR, BEN.

12:36.199 --> 12:40.204
THE HELL WE SHOULD HAVE.
NOT WITHOUT A LAWYER
TELLING ME I HAVE TO.

12:40.204 --> 12:42.707
LOOK, WE'VE GOT
RIGHTS HERE.

12:42.707 --> 12:46.210
AND WHEREVER HE IS,
WHATEVER THEY THINK HE DID,
JACOB HAS RIGHTS TOO.

12:46.210 --> 12:48.713
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO TAKE THIS
ONE STEP AT A TIME, OKAY?

12:48.713 --> 12:51.715
YOU AND I WILL LOOK
IN THE HOUSE.
TOP TO BOTTOM.

12:51.715 --> 12:53.718
I'LL CHECK OUT
THE GARAGE AND STUDIO.

12:53.718 --> 12:57.221
AND IF HE'S NOT THERE, WE'LL
JUST START CALLING HIS FRIENDS.
CAROLYN.

12:57.221 --> 12:59.723
BETTER CALL
WENDELL TOO. HUH?

13:23.246 --> 13:24.749
[ Squeaking ]

13:51.775 --> 13:55.279
[ Chuckles, Grunts ]

14:00.283 --> 14:02.286
[ Sniffles ]

14:43.828 --> 14:47.330
[ Panting ]

14:47.330 --> 14:49.834
[ Panting ]

14:53.837 --> 14:55.840
OH, NO.

14:57.842 --> 15:00.344
[ Panting ]
OH, JAKE.

15:01.845 --> 15:06.350
[ Panting ]

15:06.350 --> 15:08.768
I KNOW THAT, WENDELL.

15:09.269 --> 15:11.772
[ Judith ]
MOM?
WAIT, WAIT.

15:11.772 --> 15:14.275
WHEN FRAN COMES BACK,
WE'LL BE PERFECTLY--

15:18.278 --> 15:21.282
[ Carolyn ]
I KNOW IT'S A SMALL TOWN,
BUT IT'S OUR TOWN TOO.

15:23.783 --> 15:26.286
HE WILL. I PROMISE.
I PROMISE.

15:26.286 --> 15:28.289
JUST HURRY, OKAY?

15:28.789 --> 15:31.291
LAWYERS.
MOM?

15:31.291 --> 15:35.296
YEAH.
JACOB WAS REALLY MAD
THIS MORNING.

15:35.296 --> 15:37.298
SAID HE MIGHT NOT
EVEN GO TO SCHOOL.

15:42.303 --> 15:44.305
WHY?

15:46.306 --> 15:47.807
WHAT HAPPENED?

15:49.810 --> 15:53.314
HE AND DADDY, WELL--

15:53.314 --> 15:56.316
YOU KNOW, THEY,
THEY HAD ANOTHER FIGHT.

15:58.819 --> 16:01.322
WHAT?

16:01.821 --> 16:04.825
YOU KNOW THAT JACOB
WANTS TO RENT A BIG CAR
FOR THE WINTER DANCE...

16:05.326 --> 16:07.328
AND, LIKE, RIDE AROUND
ALL NIGHT?

16:08.829 --> 16:11.331
SO DADDY GOES,
"HOW ARE YOU PLANNING
TO PAY FOR IT?

16:11.831 --> 16:13.834
"WE'VE GOT RULES ABOUT
THIS SORT OF THING, MISTER.

16:14.335 --> 16:17.337
IT'S TIME YOU LEARN TO PAY
YOUR OWN WAY, JACOB."

16:17.337 --> 16:20.841
MOM, HE KNOWS JAKE
COULD NEVER SAVE UP
IN TIME. HE KNOWS THAT.

16:20.841 --> 16:23.344
MM-HMM.
BUT, LIKE, JAKE'S
SUCH A BIG DOPE.

16:23.344 --> 16:26.346
HE ALREADY PROMISED RIDES
TO ALL HIS CREEPY FRIENDS.

16:26.346 --> 16:29.850
HE'S ALREADY BRAGGED
ABOUT IT TO MARTH--
MARTHA?

16:30.851 --> 16:33.853
YOU KNEW ABOUT THIS GIRL?

16:33.853 --> 16:35.856
JUDE, HOW LONG HAVE
THEY BEEN GOING OUT?

16:35.856 --> 16:38.359
SINCE SEPTEMBER.

16:39.360 --> 16:41.861
BUT HE MADE ME SWEAR
I WOULDN'T TELL.

16:44.865 --> 16:49.369
JAKE SAID TO DADDY,
"YOU THINK 'CAUSE YOU'RE
THIS BIG ARTIST,

16:49.369 --> 16:52.373
IT'S LIKE RULES DON'T APPLY
TO YOU, BUT THEY SHOULD
ALWAYS APPLY TO ME."

16:52.373 --> 16:54.874
"YOU'RE A HYPOCRITE,"
JAKE SAID.

16:58.379 --> 17:01.382
AND THEN DADDY--
DADDY JUST TOTALLY LOST IT.

17:02.383 --> 17:04.384
BUT IT WAS
NEVER THAT BAD.

17:08.888 --> 17:12.392
OH.
MOM, I'M SO SCARED.

17:12.392 --> 17:15.396
HMM.
YOU DIDN'T SEE
THEIR FACES.

17:15.396 --> 17:18.397
YOU WEREN'T THERE.

17:18.397 --> 17:24.405
WELL, DADDY JUST-- HE WANTS
JACOB TO BE MORE RESPONSIBLE, SO
HE TRIES TO CHALLENGE HIS PRIDE.

17:24.405 --> 17:26.906
MAYBE TOO HARD SOMETIMES,
BUT THAT'S LOVE, JUDE.

17:27.406 --> 17:30.411
[ Sobbing ]
YOU KNOW?
THAT'S LOVE.

17:50.930 --> 17:53.934
[ Sighs ]

18:08.982 --> 18:10.984
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GO!
OKAY.

18:58.531 --> 19:01.535
[ Panting ]

19:03.036 --> 19:08.040
[ Sirens Wailing ]

20:01.259 --> 20:04.263
[ Fran ] I'LL GO ON
UP TO THE HOUSE!
[ Judith ] MOM!

20:11.771 --> 20:13.772
[ Pounding
On The Door ]
OH.

20:30.288 --> 20:32.290
WHAT ARE YA DOIN', BEN?

20:33.292 --> 20:35.294
HAVING A LOOK
AT MY CAR.

20:41.300 --> 20:44.302
DON'T I HAVE A RIGHT
TO BE IN MY OWN GARAGE?

20:44.302 --> 20:47.305
HOW LONG YOU
BEEN OUT HERE?

20:47.305 --> 20:49.809
COUPLE OF MINUTES.

20:49.809 --> 20:53.812
ALL I DID WAS LOOK AROUND,
AND I SURE DIDN'T SEE
ANYTHING WRONG EITHER.

20:55.815 --> 20:58.818
- KEYS, BEN.
- WHAT ABOUT THE WARRANT?

21:00.819 --> 21:02.821
OH, BEN--
[ Sighs ]

21:04.323 --> 21:06.325
YOU ARE ASKIN'
FOR TROUBLE ON THIS.

21:08.827 --> 21:11.831
[ Sighs ]
YOU'RE NOT THINKIN' CLEAR.

21:11.831 --> 21:15.834
NOW, HOW CAN I
HELP YOU IF YOU
DON'T EVEN TRUST ME?

21:15.834 --> 21:17.836
IT'S ALL YOURS.

21:25.844 --> 21:27.346
[ Trunk Lid Opening ]

21:27.847 --> 21:31.850
[ Policemen Talking,
Indistinct ]

21:33.351 --> 21:35.354
THIS ALWAYS SUCH A MESS?

21:36.856 --> 21:40.859
[ Ben ]
I'VE GOT SUPPLIES
TO MOVE AROUND. ART STUFF.

21:44.363 --> 21:46.364
I CAN'T USE CAROLYN'S CAR.
SHE HAS A FIT.

21:46.865 --> 21:49.869
AND THE JEEP'S TOO SMALL.
[ Clattering ]

21:53.371 --> 21:55.373
WHAT ABOUT THE FLOOR?

21:56.374 --> 21:58.878
WHERE'D ALL THIS SAWDUST
COME FROM--

21:58.878 --> 22:03.381
ALL THESE LITTLE PIECES
OF NEW WOOD?

22:03.882 --> 22:07.386
[ Sighs ]
YOU THINK I'M STUPID, BEN?
YOU THINK I'M QUAINT?

22:07.386 --> 22:10.388
OKAY. SO I LOOKED IN THERE.

22:10.388 --> 22:13.392
MAYBE SOME SAWDUST
DRIFTED OUT. IS THAT A CRIME?

22:15.393 --> 22:17.395
[ Sighs ]

22:21.400 --> 22:23.401
THIS CAR IS
OFFICIALLY IMPOUNDED.

22:25.403 --> 22:27.907
[ Sighs ]
AND I WANNA
TELL YOU SOMETHIN'.

22:29.408 --> 22:32.410
IF IT TURNS OUT
YOUR KID IS IN TROUBLE,

22:32.911 --> 22:35.414
THEN YOU ARE
IN TROUBLE TOO.

22:35.414 --> 22:37.917
NOW LET'S HAVE
A LOOK AT HIS ROOM.

22:37.917 --> 22:40.919
YOU'RE SEARCHING JACOB'S
ROOM? [ Chuckles ]
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT I AM.

22:43.923 --> 22:46.925
[ Fran ]
OHH.
[ Ben ] HEY, IF YOU
FIND HIS BED, LET US KNOW.

22:46.925 --> 22:49.427
WE HAVEN'T SEEN IT
IN YEARS.
I DON'T LIKE
YOUR ATTITUDE.

22:49.427 --> 22:53.932
IT'S NOT EXACTLY WHAT
I WOULD CALL DECENT,
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

22:53.932 --> 22:57.435
WELL, WE HAVEN'T HAD
MUCH PRACTICE, FRAN,
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

22:59.438 --> 23:02.941
ALL RIGHT, I WANNA LOOK
IN THAT CLOSET, BUT FIRST
I WANNA LOOK IN THIS TRUNK.

23:06.445 --> 23:08.947
[ Fran ]
CHECK THE BOTTOM
OF THIS, INCLUDING HERE.

23:10.448 --> 23:12.450
NOW LET'S GET THE BED.

23:22.461 --> 23:24.963
[ Fran Talking,
Indistinct ]

23:38.477 --> 23:41.479
[ Fran ] FINISH UP
IN HERE, WILL YOU?
[ Police Officer ] YEAH.

23:46.485 --> 23:48.987
OH--

23:52.491 --> 23:54.492
HEY. EXCUSE US.

23:55.994 --> 23:58.496
"THE PREMISES,"
"THE OCCUPANT,"
"A SEARCH--"

23:58.496 --> 24:00.499
NOW MAYBE YOU SEE WHY
I DIDN'T JUST FALL INTO LINE.

24:00.499 --> 24:03.501
IT'S SO STUPID AND USELESS.
WHY AREN'T THEY OUT
LOOKING FOR HIM?

24:14.012 --> 24:17.016
WELL, NOW.

24:19.017 --> 24:21.519
HIDDEN IN
HIS TOP DRAWER.

24:23.022 --> 24:25.023
[ Ben ]
SO?
SO...

24:25.023 --> 24:27.025
THAT'S A LINK,
DON'T YOU THINK?

24:27.525 --> 24:30.529
THIS PROVES THAT
THEY KNEW EACH OTHER.

24:30.529 --> 24:34.032
FRAN, NOBODY'S PRETENDING
THEY DIDN'T.

24:34.032 --> 24:36.034
SORRY I'M LATE.
I'M SO SORRY.

24:36.534 --> 24:40.538
-IFTHAT'S EVEN HER.
- OH, IT'S HER, WENDELL.
IT IS MARTHA TAVERNER.

24:40.538 --> 24:42.540
HERE'S
THE SEARCH WARRANT.

24:42.540 --> 24:45.043
WELL, I WANT A COMPLETE
INVENTORY OF ALL THE ITEMS...

24:45.043 --> 24:48.046
THAT YOU'RE REMOVING
FROM THIS HOUSE,
WITH A SIGNED RECEIPT.

24:49.547 --> 24:51.549
COME ON UP!
OKAY!

25:03.061 --> 25:05.063
OH, CAROLYN.

25:05.063 --> 25:07.065
UH, ONE MORE THING.

25:08.567 --> 25:12.070
WHEN DID YOU LOAN JACOB
YOUR TIRE JACK?

25:12.070 --> 25:14.072
MY--

25:16.075 --> 25:19.077
WELL, I'M JUST WONDERING
WHY A BEAT-UP OLD CHEVY...

25:19.077 --> 25:21.579
HAS THE JACK
FROM A '94 PARK AVENUE.

25:21.579 --> 25:24.083
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
HOLD ON.
DON'T ANSWER THAT.

25:24.083 --> 25:28.586
FRAN, FISHING SEASON STARTS
IN APRIL. LET'S YOU AND I
GO OUTSIDE AND TALK, HUH?

25:28.586 --> 25:31.089
[ Fran ]
LOOK, JACOB, MAY NOT
EVEN HAVE BEEN THERE,

25:31.089 --> 25:34.092
BUT THEY ARE PUTTING
THEMSELVES IN FRONT
OF THE LAW, WENDELL.

25:34.092 --> 25:36.094
THAT DOES NOT HELP ANYBODY.
YOU SEEM TO BE CONDUCTING
A FULL INVESTIGATION.

25:36.594 --> 25:38.596
[ Fran ]
I'M JUST SAYIN' THAT
AS A FRIEND.

25:38.596 --> 25:41.599
[ Door Closes ]
CAROLYN.
PLEASE, COME HERE.

25:41.599 --> 25:44.102
[ Fran, Wendell
CONTINUE CONVERSING,
Indistinct ]

25:44.102 --> 25:47.106
WHAT-- WHAT DOES HE MEAN--
LISTEN, LISTEN,
LISTEN TO ME!

25:48.607 --> 25:50.608
THERE WAS BLOOD
IN THE CAR.
BLOOD?

25:50.608 --> 25:52.610
HER BLOOD ON HIS JACK.
BLOOD EVERYWHERE.

25:52.610 --> 25:55.114
HOW DO YOU KNOW
IT WAS HER BLOOD?
[ Inhaling Deeply ]

25:55.114 --> 25:58.116
[ Carolyn ]
FOR GOD'S SAKE,
IT MIGHT BE HIS.

25:58.116 --> 26:00.618
SHOW ME. I WANNA SEE IT.
NO, NO, NO.
YOU DON'T WANT TO.

26:01.119 --> 26:04.622
BELIEVE ME. ANYWAY,
IT'S BEEN TAKEN CARE OF.

26:04.622 --> 26:07.125
WH-- WHAT?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"TAKEN CARE OF"?

26:07.125 --> 26:09.127
WHATEVER WOULD BURN,
I BURNED.

26:09.627 --> 26:11.130
THE JACK I TOOK APART.
I WASHED IT CLEAN.
OH, NO.

26:11.630 --> 26:14.132
BUT THERE WAS NO TIME TO--
THEY MIGHT FIND SOMETHING
ANYWAY.

26:14.132 --> 26:16.134
FIBERS OR SOME
LITTLE MICROSCOPIC--

26:16.134 --> 26:19.138
GOD ONLY KNOWS WHAT SORT
OF TESTS THEY'VE GOT NOW.
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

26:19.138 --> 26:21.139
IF WE JUST HAD
MORE TIME.
YOU CAN'T JUST--

26:21.139 --> 26:23.641
YOU CAN'T JUST DESTROY EVIDENCE
THAT MIGHT SAVE HIM.

26:23.641 --> 26:27.145
YOU CAN'T JUST-- WHAT IF
YOU'VE DESTROYED EVIDENCE
THAT WOULD PROVE HE'S INNOCENT?

26:29.647 --> 26:31.649
BEN, PLEASE,
JUST STOP ONE MINUTE.

26:32.150 --> 26:35.153
PLEASE.
WE HAVE TO THINK.

26:35.153 --> 26:38.656
WE HAVE TO DECIDE.
WHAT? WHAT HAVE WE
GOT TO DECIDE?

26:40.158 --> 26:42.161
NOTHING'S GONNA BRING
THAT GIRL BACK.

26:42.660 --> 26:44.662
I'M SORRY, BUT IT'S
TOO LATE. WE'VE GOT
TO THINK OF JACOB!

26:44.662 --> 26:47.665
BUT JACOB'S INNOCENT.
JACOB'S NOT A KILLER.

26:47.665 --> 26:49.668
IF ANYTHING,
HE'S IN DANGER HIMSELF.

26:50.168 --> 26:52.170
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT THEY
WERE ALONE IN THAT CAR?

26:52.170 --> 26:56.175
SOMEONE ELSE MIGHT HAVE
BEEN THERE AND KILLED
THAT GIRL AND TAKEN JACOB.

26:56.175 --> 26:59.677
AND NOW YOU'RE DOING
EVERYTHING YOU CAN TO KEEP
THE POLICE FROM FINDING HIM.

26:59.677 --> 27:04.183
AND WHAT IF IT WAS
JUST AN ACCIDENT, AND JACOB'S
OFF RUNNING SCARED?

27:04.183 --> 27:06.684
WE DON'T KNOW
THE FACTS, BEN.

27:07.185 --> 27:08.686
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED.

27:09.187 --> 27:11.690
[ Tow Truck Pulling Away ]

27:13.691 --> 27:17.195
OKAY, THEY'RE GONE.
YOU WANNA TELL ME
WHATEVER IT IS YOU KNOW?

27:21.199 --> 27:24.202
[ Wendell ]
HEY, HEY, HEY. LOOK,
LOOK. I'M YOUR FRIEND.

27:24.202 --> 27:26.705
AND I LOVE JACOB.
JESUS.

27:26.705 --> 27:28.706
SAT THROUGH EVERY
DAMN CLASS PLAY OF HIS.

27:29.207 --> 27:32.210
I GAVE HIM 50 BUCKS
LAST YEAR FOR THE BIKE-A-THON.

27:33.211 --> 27:36.214
I'M ON YOUR SIDE.

27:36.214 --> 27:39.717
- WENDELL, THERE IS
SOMETHING YOU SHOULD KNOW.
- HEY!

27:40.218 --> 27:43.721
WHAT IS THAT?
WHAT IS THAT, BEN RYAN?

27:44.222 --> 27:48.226
ARE YOU GONNA PRESUME NOW
TO TELL ME WHEN I CAN SPEAK
AND WHEN I HAVE TO BE QUIET?

27:48.226 --> 27:51.229
- YOU CAN KEEP YOUR OWN TONGUE
IF YOU WANT TO, BUT YOU--
- [ Phone Ringing ]

27:51.729 --> 27:53.731
JACOB!

27:55.233 --> 27:58.736
HELLO? YES.
WHO IS THIS?

28:01.739 --> 28:04.242
[ Sighs ]

28:04.242 --> 28:07.745
UH-- WELL, I HOPE YOU SLEEP
WELL TONIGHT. YOU'RE A PERSON
OF TRUE COMPASSION.

28:07.745 --> 28:11.249
CAROLYN, IT'S BETTER
IF YOU JUST HANG UP.
YES, IT'S
OUR FIRST WELL-WISHER.

28:11.249 --> 28:13.252
YES, YOU ARE.
AREN'T YOU PROUD?

28:14.252 --> 28:17.255
OH. WELL, YOU HAVEN'T
GOT MUCH OF A BRAIN,

28:17.255 --> 28:20.259
BUT YOU'VE GOT
MIGHTY Q-QUICK REFLEXES.

28:20.259 --> 28:24.262
[ Panting, Sobbing ]

28:24.262 --> 28:25.763
IT'S OKAY, HONEY.

28:25.763 --> 28:27.766
IT'S OKAY.

28:29.267 --> 28:33.271
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
[ Sobbing ]

28:33.771 --> 28:35.274
IT'S OKAY.

28:35.774 --> 28:40.278
[ Carolyn Sobbing ]

29:23.153 --> 29:26.657
[ Panting ]

29:27.157 --> 29:29.661
MA'AM?
[ Gasps ]

29:29.661 --> 29:32.663
THE-- WE'VE BEEN
ALL OVER THIS AREA AND...

29:32.663 --> 29:35.165
SOMEBODY JUST
BURIED THEIR DOG THERE.

29:35.165 --> 29:38.168
OH.
WE DUG IT UP
AND PUT IT BACK.

30:22.212 --> 30:24.715
[ Carolyn ]
I'M GOING BACK TO WORK.

30:26.216 --> 30:28.719
WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

30:30.722 --> 30:32.723
THIS IS CRAZY.

30:35.726 --> 30:38.229
WELL, I HAVE TO
LIVE MY LIFE.

30:38.229 --> 30:42.232
AND THIS TOWN HAS ITS NEEDS TOO.
DOESN'T JUST REVOLVE AROUND US
AND OUR PROBLEMS.

30:44.735 --> 30:47.738
I'LL EITHER BE BACK
IN 15 MINUTES
WITH A BLACK EYE...

30:47.738 --> 30:50.240
OR I'LL BE THERE ALL DAY.

30:50.240 --> 30:52.242
HEY.
HMM?

30:52.242 --> 30:54.244
I LOVE YOU.

30:57.748 --> 30:59.750
I LOVE YOU.

31:02.252 --> 31:04.254
BYE.
GOOD-BYE.

31:08.760 --> 31:12.262
[ Church Bell Tolling ]

31:12.262 --> 31:16.267
[ Bell Tolling ]
[ Children Chattering ]

31:23.775 --> 31:25.275
[ Chattering Stops ]

31:30.280 --> 31:32.783
[ Loud Sobbing ]
[ Woman ]
SLOW IT DOWN, OKAY?

32:09.821 --> 32:11.321
[ Groans ]

32:23.333 --> 32:25.336
[ Carolyn ]
JACOB!

32:36.847 --> 32:39.349
WHAT IF WE NEVER
SEE HIM AGAIN?

32:42.853 --> 32:44.354
OH, DARLING.

32:46.356 --> 32:50.861
NO, DON'T LOSE FAITH.
WE JUST HAVE TO BELIEVE
THAT SOMEHOW HE'LL--

32:51.361 --> 32:53.864
HE'LL FIND HIS WAY
BACK TO US. HE WILL.

32:55.867 --> 32:59.369
AND THERE IS SOME OTHER
EXPLANATION FOR ALL THIS.
I KNOW THERE IS.

33:00.370 --> 33:02.372
I KNOW IT.

33:36.406 --> 33:39.910
"DEAR FOLKS, TOOK A LONG TIME
TO GET TO BOSTON...

33:39.910 --> 33:41.912
"IN THE BIG STORM.

33:41.912 --> 33:44.915
"WASN'T SURE WE'D MAKE IT.
I MIGHT MOVE ON.

33:44.915 --> 33:46.917
"I MIGHT HANG OUT HERE
A WHILE.

33:46.917 --> 33:49.920
WILL TRY TO WRITE.
I KNOW YOU DON'T PRAY,
BUT PRAY NOW."

33:52.422 --> 33:55.425
POSTMARKED
THE DAY BEFORE YESTERDAY.

33:55.425 --> 33:59.930
CAROLYN, HE'S ALIVE.
THIS IS CRAZY.
THIS ISN'T JACOB.

33:59.930 --> 34:02.933
THAT'S HIS HANDWRITING.
NO, NO, NO.
SOMEBODY MADE HIM WRITE THIS.

34:03.433 --> 34:05.936
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?
THE POINT IS, AT LEAST
RIGHT NOW, HE'S OKAY.

34:05.936 --> 34:08.438
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
I'M CALLING FRAN.
I-I THINK IT'S IMPORTANT.

34:08.938 --> 34:11.942
FRAN? CAROLYN,
LISTEN TO ME. WILL YOU
JUST LISTEN TO ME?

34:12.442 --> 34:15.445
IF FRAN SEES THIS,
THE FIRST THING HE'LL DO
IS GET A COURT ORDER...

34:15.445 --> 34:17.447
TO INTERCEPT OUR MAIL
AND TAP OUR PHONES.

34:17.447 --> 34:20.449
THEN YOU CAN FORGET
ABOUT EVER HEARING
FROM JAKE AGAIN.

34:20.449 --> 34:23.453
AND THAT'S JUST
FOR STARTERS.

34:23.453 --> 34:25.956
THEY'LL SLAP A MANHUNT
ALL OVER BOSTON.

34:26.456 --> 34:28.958
HE'LL RUN AGAIN.
GOD KNOWS WHERE.

34:28.958 --> 34:32.462
THINK ABOUT IT.
DO WE REALLY
WANT HIM CAUGHT?

34:35.966 --> 34:40.469
I-- I JUST WANT MY BOY BACK.
I JUST WANNA HOLD HIM AGAIN.

34:40.469 --> 34:43.473
I JUST--
I JUST WANT MY BOY.

34:43.473 --> 34:45.976
OH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

34:45.976 --> 34:48.478
[ Weeping ]

34:51.197 --> 34:54.199
[ Register Rings ]
THAT'S OUT OF 30.

34:57.704 --> 34:59.706
TWENTY-SIX, TWENTY-SEVEN,
TWENTY-EIGHT...
IS THAT WHO I THINK IT IS?

34:59.706 --> 35:01.708
TWENTY-NINE, THIRTY.
[ Whispering ]

35:04.210 --> 35:06.212
BEN RYAN.

35:08.214 --> 35:10.216
KEEP YOUR CHIN UP,
YOU HEAR?

35:14.721 --> 35:17.223
SORRY, JOE.
ALL I NEED IS CHANGE.

35:39.245 --> 35:41.247
OH.

35:49.255 --> 35:53.259
GOOD NIGHT, KAREN.
SEE YOU FOR MY 8:00.
UM,
MRS. WEBBER CANCELED, DOCTOR.

35:53.760 --> 35:55.261
SHE SAID
YOU'D UNDERSTAND.

35:57.764 --> 36:00.767
OKAY.
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT.

36:02.769 --> 36:05.772
HI, DOCTOR.
T.J. HI.

36:05.772 --> 36:08.775
I GOT A FEVER.
YOU GOT A FEVER?

36:08.775 --> 36:10.777
OH, WHAT YOU--
COME ON, HONEY.

36:10.777 --> 36:12.779
[ Awkward Laugh ]
I'M SORRY.

36:29.963 --> 36:33.750
ST. LOUIS ON MARCH 11.
THAT'S THE THIRD CARD.

36:33.750 --> 36:37.253
THEN HE WAS IN L.A.
JUST TWO DAYS LATER.
HI.

36:39.756 --> 36:41.758
IT'S A NEW ONE.
CALIFORNIA.

36:47.263 --> 36:50.266
WHAT'S THIS DOING OUT?
THIS SPOILS.

36:53.770 --> 36:56.773
THAT'S IT? THAT'S
YOUR WHOLE REACTION?

36:56.773 --> 36:59.275
LOOK, YOU WON'T SHOW THESE
TO FRAN. ALL RIGHT.

36:59.275 --> 37:03.279
BUT YOU WON'T EVEN SHOW THEM
TO WENDELL, BENNY, AND HE'S
OUR LAWYER. HE'S OUR FRIEND.

37:03.279 --> 37:06.783
IF THIS GETS OUT,
WE DON'T KNOW HOW IT
MIGHT BE USED AGAINST HIM.

37:06.783 --> 37:10.286
MMM.
IN FACT, IT MIGHT
COME IN HANDY LATER
THAT WE KEPT QUIET.

37:10.286 --> 37:12.288
HANDY?
[ Phone Ringing ]

37:12.288 --> 37:14.290
WAIT, WAIT.

37:19.295 --> 37:22.799
HELLO. WENDELL.

37:22.799 --> 37:25.802
WHAT'S--

37:25.802 --> 37:29.305
TURN ON THE TV.
CHANNEL 3. YEAH.
YEAH, WE GOT IT.

37:29.305 --> 37:32.809
- ...CROSS AMERICA--
- ???? [ Theme Music ]
- JACOB RYAN,

37:33.309 --> 37:37.313
THE 16-YEAR-OLD HIGHLAND
RESIDENT, WHO IS A SUSPECT IN
THE MURDER OF MARTHA TAVERNER,

37:37.313 --> 37:39.315
WAS A FUGITIVE
FOR FIVE WEEKS.

37:39.315 --> 37:41.818
THE TEENAGER, AS REPORTED
MOMENTS AGO, WAS ARRESTED
THIS AFTERNOON...

37:41.818 --> 37:44.320
- [ Carolyn Gasps ]
-IN THE BUILDING
YOU SEE BEHIND ME.

37:44.320 --> 37:46.823
APPARENTLY,
THE YOUNG FUGITIVE WAS HIDING
IN A FRIEND'S APARTMENT.

37:46.823 --> 37:50.326
WE UNDERSTAND THAT HE IS NOW
BEING HELD IN THE JUVENILE
DETENTION CENTER,

37:50.326 --> 37:53.829
AND IT IS EXPECTED
THAT HE WILL BE ARRAIGNED
SOMETIME TOMORROW.

38:05.842 --> 38:07.844
[ Beeping ]

38:12.849 --> 38:14.851
THIS WAY.

38:16.852 --> 38:18.855
[ Indistinct Chatter ]

38:39.374 --> 38:41.377
JAKE. JAKE!

38:41.377 --> 38:44.380
HI, SON.
OH, THANK GOD
YOU'RE SAFE.

38:50.887 --> 38:52.889
HOW ARE YOU, SON?

38:55.391 --> 38:58.394
WHERE WERE YOU?

38:58.394 --> 39:00.897
JAKE, FIRST OFF,
YOUR SISTER--

39:00.897 --> 39:04.400
SHE WANTED US TO ASK YOU,
UM, IF THE POSTCARDS--

39:04.400 --> 39:09.405
W-WERE YOU REALLY IN
ALL THOSE PLACES, JAKE?

39:09.405 --> 39:12.408
OR WERE YOU HERE THE WHOLE TIME
IN YOUR FRIEND DARREN'S
APARTMENT, HUH?

39:18.414 --> 39:20.416
YOUR DAD ASKED YOU
A QUESTION.

39:22.418 --> 39:24.420
HONEY, ARE YOU
GONNA TALK TO US?

39:27.423 --> 39:30.426
YOU DON'T THINK YOU'RE GONNA
BE ABLE TO HOLD OUT LIKE THIS
FOREVER, DO YOU, JAKE?

39:30.426 --> 39:33.930
POLICEMEN CAN'T HEAR YOU.
AND WE HAVE TOLD THEM NOTHING.

39:35.932 --> 39:37.934
ARE YOU STILL
MAD AT ME?

39:39.435 --> 39:42.939
IS THAT IT?
YOU KNOW YOUR FATHER
HAS STOOD UP FOR YOU.

39:42.939 --> 39:45.441
TELL ME, PLEASE.
DO YOU
REALIZE THAT?

39:48.443 --> 39:50.947
JAKIE!
GODDAMN IT, MISTER.

39:50.947 --> 39:53.950
HAVE YOU ANY IDEA WHAT
YOU'VE PUT US THROUGH?
MAYBE HE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW.

39:53.950 --> 39:56.451
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHY YOU'RE HERE?
HAVE THEY TOLD YOU?

39:56.451 --> 39:58.454
DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO MARTHA TAVERNER?

39:58.454 --> 40:00.957
THERE IS A WARRANT FOR YOU
BACK IN HIGHLAND.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

40:00.957 --> 40:05.962
YOU MAY BE ABLE TO COME HOME.
FIRST, THEY JUST HAVE TO HAVE
A HEARING IN FRONT OF A JUDGE.

40:05.962 --> 40:09.966
A-AND WENDELL BYE WILL BE
RIGHT THERE WITH YOU, AND
DADDY AND I WILL BE RIGHT THERE.

40:09.966 --> 40:12.969
AND YOU BETTER SPEAK UP THEN,
JAKE, IN COURT.

40:13.469 --> 40:14.971
JAKE.

40:16.973 --> 40:19.474
CAN YOU LOOK AT US?

40:20.476 --> 40:22.478
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

40:32.989 --> 40:37.493
DO SOME THINKING ABOUT WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA SAY TO WENDELL.
DON'T WASTE HIS TIME TOO.

40:57.512 --> 40:59.515
LET'S GO.

41:11.027 --> 41:13.361
[ Chattering ]

41:36.384 --> 41:38.386
[ Demonstrators ]
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!

41:38.386 --> 41:42.890
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!

41:42.890 --> 41:45.393
NO BAIL!
KILLERS IN JAIL!

41:45.393 --> 41:47.395
NO BAIL!
KILLERS IN JAIL!

41:47.395 --> 41:51.398
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!
NO BAIL! KILLERS IN JAIL!

41:51.398 --> 41:53.902
LOOK OUT, PLEASE.
GIVE US SOME ROOM.
LOOK OUT.

41:53.902 --> 41:58.405
[ Chanting Continues ]
WHY DID YOU KILL HER?

42:00.408 --> 42:03.411
JACOB RYAN, YOU'VE HEARD
THE CHARGE AGAINST YOU.

42:03.411 --> 42:09.417
IN JUVENILE PROCEEDINGS,
WE ENTER A PLEA OF "TRUE"
OR "NOT TRUE."

42:09.417 --> 42:11.920
HOW SAY YOU
TO THIS CHARGE?

42:13.921 --> 42:17.425
NOT TRUE.
[ Demonstrators Chanting ]

42:21.428 --> 42:24.933
JACOB RYAN
IS A LONGTIME RESIDENT.

42:24.933 --> 42:28.435
HE'S A FINE STUDENT.
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN
OF FLAWLESS CHARACTER.

42:28.435 --> 42:31.439
AND HE IS STILL,
AT THE MOMENT, A MINOR,

42:31.439 --> 42:35.943
AND, THEREFORE,
WE RESPECTFULLY REQUEST
THAT HE BE RELEASED ON BOND.

42:36.443 --> 42:38.446
JACOB RYAN
IS CHARGED...

42:38.947 --> 42:42.951
WITH A TERRIBLE AND
ALMOST UNTHINKABLE CRIME.

42:42.951 --> 42:47.956
MOREOVER, THE PEOPLE
WILL PROVE THAT HE
EXACERBATED THAT CRIME...

42:47.956 --> 42:49.958
AFTER THE FACT...

42:49.958 --> 42:55.463
BY HIS CUNNING, DELIBERATE
AND COLD-BLOODED DESTRUCTION
OF EVIDENCE.

42:57.966 --> 43:00.468
NO PARENT
IN THIS TOWN...

43:00.468 --> 43:03.471
AND SURELY NO DAUGHTER
COULD FEEL SAFE...

43:03.972 --> 43:06.974
WITH JACOB RYAN
ON THE LOOSE AGAIN.

43:06.974 --> 43:09.978
THE PEOPLE URGE
THAT BAIL BE DENIED.

43:11.479 --> 43:13.981
MARION, I'M JUST
NOT PERSUADED...

43:13.981 --> 43:17.986
THIS BOY IS A THREAT
TO THE GENERAL COMMUNITY.

43:18.486 --> 43:23.491
YOUR HONOR,
I WAS ALSO THINKING
OF THEIR THREAT TO HIM.

43:25.493 --> 43:27.996
DEFENDANT, PLEASE RISE.

43:30.497 --> 43:33.001
PRETRIAL RELEASE GRANTED.

43:34.502 --> 43:37.504
BOND SET AT $250,000.

43:38.505 --> 43:42.510
?? YOU SAY YOU FEEL
SO DISTORTED ??

43:42.510 --> 43:45.512
]
???? [ Continues, Indistinct

43:50.018 --> 43:54.022
NOW LISTEN, MISTER. YOU CAN DO
WHATEVER THE HELL YOU WANT
WITH YOUR CATATONIC SELF,

43:54.022 --> 43:56.024
BUT DON'T EVEN THINK
ABOUT OPENING THIS DOOR.

43:56.524 --> 43:58.526
YOU HEAR ME?
[ Whispering ]
OH, BEN.

43:58.526 --> 44:01.528
JUDE!

44:01.528 --> 44:04.032
JACOB!
I MADE YOU SOME COOKIES!

44:10.038 --> 44:13.541
- JACOB?
-[ Carolyn ]
MAYBE YOU--

44:13.541 --> 44:17.045
MAYBE YOU WANNA HAVE
SOME SOUP FIRST OR S--

44:17.045 --> 44:19.047
A SANDWICH OR SOMETHING.

44:21.049 --> 44:23.550
MOM, WHAT'S WRONG
WITH HIM?

44:26.554 --> 44:29.557
I THINK WE JUST HAVE TO
GIVE HIM A FEW DAYS, SWEETIE.

44:37.065 --> 44:39.066
WHEN WE FOUGHT
THAT MORNING,

44:42.070 --> 44:44.572
I RAISED MY FIST
TO HIM.

44:44.572 --> 44:46.573
I WOULD'VE HIT HIM.

44:46.573 --> 44:49.077
AND WE BOTH
KNEW IT, CAROLYN.

44:52.580 --> 44:55.583
I SENT HIM OUT
INTO THE WORLD
IN THAT KIND OF RAGE.

44:57.085 --> 45:01.588
BUT YOU DIDN'T, BENNY.
YOU DIDN'T HIT HIM.

45:01.588 --> 45:05.593
AND PEOPLE DO FIGHT.
THEY ARGUE ALL THE TIME.

45:05.593 --> 45:09.096
IF I'M TO BLAME
FOR THIS, HOW CAN I
EVER MAKE IT UP TO HIM?

45:09.096 --> 45:11.099
NO.

45:11.599 --> 45:14.102
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED YET.

45:15.603 --> 45:18.105
IF WE START BLAMING
OURSELVES, OR, OR EACH OTHER,

45:18.105 --> 45:20.608
HOW ARE WE
GONNA GET THROUGH THIS?

45:24.111 --> 45:28.116
WHEN HE'S READY
AND WHEN HE'S ABLE, HE'LL
TELL US WHAT HAPPENED. HE WILL.

45:29.117 --> 45:31.618
RIGHT NOW...

45:31.618 --> 45:35.123
THE ONLY IMPORTANT THING
IS THAT WE'RE ALL TOGETHER
AGAIN AND HE'S HOME.

45:39.126 --> 45:41.629
HE'S HOME.
HE'S HOME.

46:33.180 --> 46:35.183
[ Whimpering ]

46:37.185 --> 46:39.687
[ Weeping ]

46:39.687 --> 46:41.688
[ Wendell ]
THEY GOT EYEWITNESSES.

46:41.688 --> 46:46.194
THEY'RE NOT CLAIMING
TO HAVE SOMEONE WHO
ACTUALLY SAW THE MURDER.

46:46.194 --> 46:49.696
AT LEAST NOT YET.
THEN WHAT, EXACTLY, DO THESE
PEOPLE CLAIM TO HAVE SEEN?

46:49.696 --> 46:53.701
THE TWO OF THEM
IN HIS CAR, I WOULD GUESS.

46:54.202 --> 46:57.704
HIS CAR STOPPED MAYBE
UP ON, UH, POOR FARM ROAD?

47:01.209 --> 47:05.713
PROSECUTOR SAYS THEY HAVE PROOF
THAT JACOB DESTROYED EVIDENCE.

47:05.713 --> 47:08.716
WELL, SHE
HAS TO SAY THAT,
DOESN'T SHE?

47:08.716 --> 47:12.219
- THEY STILL HAVEN'T FOUND
THE MURDER WEAPON.
- BUT, BUT SURELY...

47:12.219 --> 47:14.222
THAT HELPS OUR, OUR CASE.

47:14.222 --> 47:17.225
- I MEAN, YOU'RE SAYING THAT
THEY'VE GOT A LOUSY CASE.
- CIRCUMSTANTIAL, YES.

47:17.225 --> 47:19.226
I'M SAYIN' THAT'S POSSIBLE.

47:19.226 --> 47:22.730
THEN I DON'T UNDERSTAND,
WENDELL. WHY ARE YOU
DROPPING OUT ON US?

47:23.731 --> 47:26.733
[ Ironic Laugh ]
I WOULDN'T, UH--

47:28.736 --> 47:30.738
IT'S NOT THAT.

47:32.240 --> 47:34.741
LOOK, I-I--

47:34.741 --> 47:37.245
I DO MORTGAGE CLOSINGS.

47:37.745 --> 47:39.247
YOU NEED
AN EXPERT NOW.

47:39.747 --> 47:41.748
CRIMINAL GUY.

47:41.748 --> 47:45.253
AND BELIEVE ME, THIS GUY
I'M TELLIN' YOU ABOUT--

47:45.253 --> 47:47.255
HE IS THE BEST.

47:47.255 --> 47:49.256
UH, PANOS DEMERIS.

47:49.256 --> 47:51.759
GREEK-AMERICAN.
LIVES OVER IN SPRINGFIELD.

47:57.764 --> 48:00.268
HE'S LOST MAYBE ONE CASE
IN HIS WHOLE LIFE.

48:02.270 --> 48:05.772
HE'LL HAVE JACOB'S JURY
VOTING FOR SAINTHOOD.

48:05.772 --> 48:10.778
AND WHAT ABOUT THE TRUTH
OF WHAT HAPPENED?
DOESN'T THAT MATTER?

48:13.780 --> 48:17.285
THE TRUTH, MRS. RYAN?
THE TRUTH ISN'T ALWAYS
SO SIMPLE.

48:31.799 --> 48:36.303
I JUST MEANT DO YOU HAVE TO
BELIEVE SOMEONE IS INNOCENT
IN ORDER TO TAKE HIS CASE?

48:36.303 --> 48:39.807
A LOT OF MY CLIENTS HAVEN'T BEEN
INNOCENT OF ANYTHING YOU'D CARE
TO LAY ON THEM...

48:40.308 --> 48:42.809
SINCE THEY WERE FIVE YEARS OLD,
BUT THEY STILL DESERVE
A GOOD DEFENSE, RIGHT?

48:43.310 --> 48:46.314
DO YOU MIND IF I EAT
WHILE WE TALK?

48:48.816 --> 48:52.820
IS THIS LATE LUNCH,
MR. DEMERIS, OR
EARLY DINNER?

48:53.821 --> 48:56.824
THIS IS BREAKFAST, I THINK.

48:56.824 --> 49:00.328
I HAD A PRETRIAL MEETING
AND NEVER DID STOP.

49:00.828 --> 49:03.331
OKAY, SO...
YOUR SON, JACOB.

49:05.332 --> 49:09.337
NOW FROM WHAT
YOU'VE TOLD ME, HE SEEMS
LIKE A PRETTY REGULAR KID.

49:09.337 --> 49:12.839
I MEAN EVEN THESE SILENCES,
YOU KNOW? HOPING IF HE
HANGS TOUGH LONG ENOUGH,

49:13.340 --> 49:15.843
MAYBE THIS WHOLE THING
WILL JUST DISAPPEAR?

49:15.843 --> 49:18.346
[ Chuckling ]
TEENAGERS, HUH?
GOD HELP US.

49:19.347 --> 49:21.348
BUT, UH, LET ME--

49:21.348 --> 49:25.353
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.
NOW, PLEASE, TAKE THIS AS
A NEUTRAL QUESTION, OKAY?

49:25.853 --> 49:29.356
IT'S NOT AN ACCUSATION
OF ANY KIND, BUT-- ANGER.

49:29.356 --> 49:33.361
DOES JACOB HAVE ANY PARTICULAR
PROBLEM EXPRESSING HIS ANGER?

49:33.361 --> 49:35.862
DOES HE TEND TO KEEP THINGS
BOTTLED UP?

49:36.363 --> 49:40.368
DOES HE EVER JUST EXPLODE?
YOU SEE, I'M ASKING YOU BECAUSE
IF THERE'S ANY HISTORY HERE,

49:40.368 --> 49:43.370
I MEAN EVEN JUST A WHIFF,
I HAVE TO HEAR IT FROM YOU.

49:43.370 --> 49:46.374
NOT SOME PROSECUTOR.
NO, HE--
THERE'S NO HISTORY.

49:46.374 --> 49:50.378
JACOB'S A VERY--
HE'S A VERY KIND PERSON.

49:50.378 --> 49:52.879
DECENT. CARING.
YOU'D LIKE HIM.
SURE, SURE.

49:53.380 --> 49:56.884
BUT YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND,
MR. AND MRS. RYAN-- I'M SORRY.
IS IT "MR." AND "DR."?

49:56.884 --> 50:00.387
BEN AND CAROLYN.
OKAY. NOW YOU
HAVE TO UNDERSTAND:

50:00.387 --> 50:04.892
JURIES, IN CASES
OF THIS NATURE, THEY TEND
TO BE VERY EMOTIONAL.

50:05.393 --> 50:09.397
THEY TEND TO FEEL THAT
WHERE THERE'S SMOKE,
THERE'S FIRE.

50:09.397 --> 50:14.401
HEY. I COULD BE UP THERE,
ARGUING THAT JACOB IS THE MOST
PERFECT KID IN THE WORLD.

50:14.401 --> 50:16.403
THAT'S ONE STRATEGY.
BUT WHAT THEY'LL BE THINKING,

50:16.403 --> 50:18.906
WHAT THEY'LL SEE
IN THEIR MIND'S EYE...

50:21.408 --> 50:23.910
AND NEVER FORGET IS THIS.

50:25.413 --> 50:27.415
YOU CAN'T--
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

50:27.415 --> 50:30.917
NO, DR. RYAN, I'M--
YOU CANNOT JUST SIT HERE AND EAT
A SANDWICH AND DISPLAY SUCH--

50:31.418 --> 50:33.421
- HOW DO YOU EXPECT US
TO SURVIVE THIS?
- DR. RYAN.

50:33.421 --> 50:35.923
I'M NOT BEING UNSYMPATHETIC.
DON'T INFER THAT.

50:35.923 --> 50:39.927
BUT THIS HAS GOT NOTHING TO DO
WITH SYMPATHY. I THOUGHT YOU
TOLD ME YOU'D SEEN THIS CORPSE.

50:39.927 --> 50:43.431
THIS IS NOT JUST ANY CORPSE.
THIS IS A GIRL THAT I KNEW,
THAT I ONCE TREATED.

50:43.431 --> 50:45.432
JUST BECAUSE YOU SEE THIS KIND
OF THING EVERY DAY--

50:45.932 --> 50:49.937
YOU SPEND ALL YOUR TIME
WITH VIOLENT, HORRIBLE PEOPLE,
BUT WE DON'T, MR. DEMERIS.

50:49.937 --> 50:51.938
NO? WELL, THEN,
YOU'RE VERY LUCKY.

50:51.938 --> 50:54.941
I'M A PHYSICIAN, AND THERE ISN'T
MUCH I HAVEN'T SEEN, BUT THIS IS
MY SON YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

50:55.443 --> 50:58.446
YOU MAY LIKE TO REMEMBER,
DR. RYAN, IT'S ALWAYS
SOMEBODY'S SON.

50:58.446 --> 51:02.449
DON'T YOU PATRONIZE ME, SIR,
BECAUSE I CAN--
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

51:02.950 --> 51:05.453
LET'S CALM DOWN.
ALL OF US. CAROLYN.

51:05.453 --> 51:09.456
THIS ISN'T
GETTING US ANYWHERE.
COME ON, HONEY.

51:09.456 --> 51:11.959
LOOK, I'M SORRY, FOLKS.

51:11.959 --> 51:14.961
BUT IF YOU DON'T
LIKE ME NOW,

51:15.462 --> 51:18.466
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA SAY
WHEN I HAVE TO GET UP
IN FRONT OF THAT JURY...

51:18.466 --> 51:23.970
AND ARGUE THAT YOUR SON
IS NOT GUILTY BY REASON OF
DIMINISHED MENTAL CAPACITY?

51:25.472 --> 51:27.475
THAT HE WAS DRUNK.
STONED.

51:27.475 --> 51:29.976
HEY, HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.
YES, BOMBED OUT OF
HIS SKULL ON CRACK.

51:30.477 --> 51:33.981
MY SON DOES NOT DO DRUGS.
HE MAY BE YOUR SON, MR. RYAN,
BUT HE WOULD BE MY CLIENT,

51:33.981 --> 51:37.484
AND I WOULD NOT ASK
YOUR PERMISSION FOR HOW
I CHOOSE TO DEFEND HIM.

51:37.484 --> 51:40.987
I'M GONNA HAVE TO DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES.

51:40.987 --> 51:45.992
AND IF YOU DON'T LIKE
MY STYLE, WAIT 'TIL
YOU HEAR THE PROSECUTION.

51:47.494 --> 51:49.997
LISTEN, DR. RYAN,
YOU WANNA JUMP IN
THE TRENCHES WITH ME?

51:49.997 --> 51:52.500
WELL, YOU BETTER MUSCLE UP.

51:52.999 --> 51:58.506
LOSE YOUR BEDSIDE MANNER
AND TRUST ME TO BE AS GOOD
AT MY JOB AS YOU ARE AT YOURS.

52:06.013 --> 52:10.517
WILL YOU DO IT, MR. DEMERIS?
WILL YOU TAKE OUR CASE?

52:12.520 --> 52:14.522
FOR YOUR SON, YEAH.

52:16.523 --> 52:19.025
YEAH, I'LL DEFEND JACOB.

52:30.037 --> 52:31.538
JAKE?

52:32.038 --> 52:35.042
I KNOW YOU DON'T
WANNA TALK, BUT I
JUST NEED TO SEE YOU.

52:38.545 --> 52:40.547
CAN I COME UP?
PLEASE?

53:09.075 --> 53:11.077
CAN I JUST ASK YOU
ONE QUESTION?

53:15.082 --> 53:17.083
DID YOU EVER REALLY
GO ANYWHERE, JAKE?

53:21.589 --> 53:25.091
OKAY. THAT'S COOL.
I UNDERSTAND.

53:27.594 --> 53:30.097
BUT JUST SO YOU KNOW,

53:30.097 --> 53:33.600
WHEN YOU WERE
IN THAT JAIL,
I TRIED TO COME.

53:34.601 --> 53:36.604
THEY WOULDN'T LET ME.

53:36.604 --> 53:39.606
JAKE, I REALLY
WANTED TO SEE YOU.

53:39.606 --> 53:43.109
THEY ACT LIKE THEY HAVE TO
PROTECT ME FROM ALL OF THIS.

53:43.109 --> 53:46.113
SURE. THEY CAN'T EVEN
PROTECT THEMSELVES.

53:48.114 --> 53:51.619
AND I HEAR PLENTY.
I KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.

53:53.120 --> 53:55.622
LIKE...

53:55.622 --> 53:58.124
MOM'S HAD TO CLOSE
HER OFFICE.

53:58.124 --> 54:00.628
SHE SAYS IT'S
JUST TEMPORARY.

54:00.628 --> 54:02.629
SURE.
GIMME A BREAK.

54:05.131 --> 54:08.135
WELL, ANYWAY,
THAT'S ALL.

54:08.135 --> 54:11.638
I JUST WANTED TO ASK
ABOUT THE POSTCARDS.
NO BIG DEAL.

54:13.640 --> 54:16.143
JUDE, WAIT. DON'T GO.

54:16.644 --> 54:21.147
ONCE OR TWICE A WEEK,
I'D TAKE THE TRAIN
OUT TO LOGAN AIRPORT.

54:21.147 --> 54:25.152
THEN I'D FIND A FLIGHT THAT WAS
GOIN' TO WHERE I WANTED TO GO.

54:25.152 --> 54:29.155
AND THEN I'D FIND SOMEBODY
THAT WOULDN'T MIND MAILING A
CARD FOR ME WHEN THEY GOT THERE.

54:31.659 --> 54:35.161
AND I SAID THAT
I'M HOME FROM VACATION,
AND I FORGOT TO SEND THIS...

54:35.662 --> 54:39.166
AND I DON'T WANT MY PARENTS
TO THINK I DON'T MISS 'EM.

54:39.667 --> 54:41.668
AND THEN, LIKE, I'D SIT
IN ONE OF THOSE CHAIRS,
YOU KNOW?

54:41.668 --> 54:44.170
IN THE WAITING AREA
AT THE AIRPORT.

54:48.175 --> 54:50.176
I'D SHUT MY EYES LIKE THIS...

54:52.178 --> 54:54.181
AND SIT.

54:57.183 --> 54:59.185
I WENT THERE WITH 'EM.

55:00.688 --> 55:03.690
I WENT TO
ALL THOSE PLACES, JUDE.

55:06.693 --> 55:09.196
YOU WON'T SAY ANYTHING,
WILL YOU?

55:09.196 --> 55:11.197
NOBODY ELSE
WOULD UNDERSTAND.

55:30.049 --> 55:32.052
[ Phone Rings ]

55:32.052 --> 55:34.053
WAIT.

55:35.555 --> 55:37.056
[ Rings ]

55:38.559 --> 55:40.561
HELLO.

55:40.561 --> 55:42.562
[ Laughs ]

55:44.063 --> 55:47.568
YES, SIR, I SEE.
OH, THAT'S VERY BIBLICAL.

55:47.568 --> 55:51.571
AND I TAKE IT
YOU WOULD LIKE TO CAST
THE FIRST ONE, HUH?

55:53.573 --> 55:56.577
NOW, I WANT YOU TO
LISTEN VERY CAREFULLY--
NO, NO, YOU LISTEN.

55:57.076 --> 55:59.579
I WANT YOU TO KNOW,
YOU GOOD CITIZEN,
THAT MY SON IS INNOCENT.

56:00.079 --> 56:03.584
HE'S A FREE YOUNG MAN,
LEGALLY HERE ON BOND,
AGAINST WHOM NOTHING HAS BEEN--

56:04.084 --> 56:05.585
NO, NO. YOU'RE WRONG.

56:06.085 --> 56:10.090
UNLESS HE'S CONVICTED
IN A COURT OF LAW, HE IS
NO MORE GUILTY THAN YOU ARE.

56:10.591 --> 56:13.593
SO SLEEP TIGHT, PAL,
AND HEY, HAVE A WONDERFUL
TIME IN CHURCH.

56:13.593 --> 56:16.095
[ Hangs Up Receiver ]

56:16.095 --> 56:18.098
YEAH, DAD.
YOU'RE SO COOL.

56:18.098 --> 56:20.099
YOU REALLY
BELIEVE THAT?

56:26.607 --> 56:29.609
WELL, OF--
OF COURSE I DO.

56:29.609 --> 56:31.611
OUR WHOLE SYSTEM
OF JUSTICE--

56:31.611 --> 56:34.114
I DON'T MEAN OUR SYSTEM.
I MEAN ABOUT ME.

56:34.114 --> 56:36.616
DO YOU BELIEVE
THAT I'M NOT GUILTY?

56:38.618 --> 56:40.621
JAKE,

56:40.621 --> 56:42.623
I DON'T KNOW.

56:42.623 --> 56:44.624
BUT--

56:44.624 --> 56:47.628
WELL, NOW THAT
YOU'RE HERE, WE CAN--

56:47.628 --> 56:49.630
WE CAN TALK ABOUT THAT.

56:49.630 --> 56:53.132
BUT WHATEVER THE TRUTH IS,
WE'RE STANDING BY YOU.

56:53.633 --> 56:56.637
ABSOLUTELY.
OH, THAT'S JUST A BUNCH
OF SENTIMENTAL BULLSHIT.

56:56.637 --> 57:00.139
I MEAN ME.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?
HEY. HEY, NOT SO FAST.

57:00.139 --> 57:02.141
[ Carolyn ]
"SENTIMENTAL BULLSHIT"?

57:02.141 --> 57:05.645
EVERYBODY'S PARENTS
SAY STUFF LIKE THAT.
DO THEY? DO THEY REALLY?

57:05.645 --> 57:09.148
AND DO THEY HIDE THE WEAPON
AND DESTROY EVIDENCE...
CAROLYN.

57:09.148 --> 57:11.151
AND LIE
TO THE POLICE?

57:11.151 --> 57:14.153
DO THEY, INDEED?
YOU KNOW THIS
FOR A FACT?

57:19.660 --> 57:23.663
HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO JUST
SIT HERE AND TALK ABOUT
KILLING SOMEBODY?

57:24.163 --> 57:27.668
JAKE, STOP RUNNING.
PLEASE.

57:28.668 --> 57:31.170
YOU'RE HOME NOW.
STOP RUNNING.

57:32.171 --> 57:35.676
IF I TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED--
IT WASN'T ME.

57:37.176 --> 57:40.680
[ Sighs ]
IT WASN'T ME, ALL RIGHT?

57:51.191 --> 57:54.193
WE HUNG OUT A LOT
THIS YEAR.

57:54.193 --> 57:57.197
I KEPT MEANING
TO TELL YOU GUYS.

57:57.197 --> 57:59.699
I WANTED YOU TO KNOW,
BUT--

57:59.699 --> 58:02.702
I TOLD MARTHA YOU GUYS
WERE COOL,

58:02.702 --> 58:06.206
BUT THE IDEA OF HAVING TO
MEET YOU, CONVERSE WITH YOU,
IT JUST SPOOKED HER SOMEHOW.

58:08.708 --> 58:12.212
THAT DAY WE HAD
A TERRIBLE ARGUMENT.

58:14.714 --> 58:19.720
[ Sighs ] FROM THE MOMENT
I PICKED HER UP AT THE
ICE CREAM SHOP AT JACEY'S,

58:19.720 --> 58:23.723
SHE WAS ON MY CASE ABOUT
NOT HAVING A RENTAL CAR
FOR THE WINTER DANCE.

58:23.723 --> 58:29.229
SHE WAS SAYING IT'S YOUR WAY,
OURS,OF FINALLY SAYING
SHE'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH FOR ME.

58:30.229 --> 58:32.231
[ Jacob Sighs ]

58:33.733 --> 58:37.236
[ Sighs ]
I-I TRIED TO EXPLAIN TO HER,
BUT SHE JUST--

58:37.737 --> 58:40.740
SHE KEPT YELLING AT ME
AS I WAS TRYING TO DRIVE.

58:40.740 --> 58:44.244
THEN SHE SAID,
"PULL OVER RIGHT HERE."

58:47.747 --> 58:49.248
[ Jacob ]
AND IT TURNS OUT,

58:49.749 --> 58:52.752
I'M NOT THE ONE
SHE'S MAD AT, REALLY.

58:52.752 --> 58:56.255
SHE'S MAD AT EVERYONE
AND EVERYTHING.

58:56.255 --> 59:00.259
GOD, ESPECIALLY,
FOR LETTING THIS HAPPEN TO HER,
'CAUSE IT TURNS OUT--

59:00.760 --> 59:02.762
I'M PREGNANT.

59:09.268 --> 59:12.271
[ Jacob ]
IT GETS EVEN MORE
COMPLICATED.

59:13.273 --> 59:16.275
'CAUSE SHE DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS OURS.

59:16.275 --> 59:20.279
SHE WOULDN'T SAY
WHOSE IT MIGHT BE, BUT...

59:20.279 --> 59:23.282
OBVIOUSLY SHE'S BEEN,
YOU KNOW--

59:25.284 --> 59:27.787
GETTING AROUND.

59:27.787 --> 59:30.290
I NEVER EVEN
HAD A CLUE.

59:30.290 --> 59:34.293
SHE FIGURED IT WASN'T
OURS BECAUSE WE WERE
ALWAYS SO CAREFUL.

59:35.795 --> 59:37.798
SO SHE'S GETTING
ALL WOUND UP.

59:37.798 --> 59:40.800
"I HATE YOU.
I NEVER WANT TO
SEE YOU AGAIN."

59:40.800 --> 59:45.805
SHE WAS EVEN MOCKING ME
FOR TAKING CARE WITH HER,
FOR USING--

59:45.805 --> 59:48.307
LIKE ONLY A WIMP
WOULD THINK AHEAD
LIKE THAT.

59:48.808 --> 59:50.810
I SAID,
"THAT'S IT. LET'S GO.

59:51.311 --> 59:55.314
"YOU CAN HAVE YOUR BABY
OR NOT; YOU CAN STAY WITH
YOUR CAVEMAN OR NOT.

59:55.314 --> 59:57.316
I DON'T CARE."

59:57.316 --> 01:00:00.821
SO THEN SHE GOT
ALL SORT OF--
[ Shifting Gears ]

01:00:00.821 --> 01:00:02.822
JAKE, WAIT.

01:00:02.822 --> 01:00:04.824
DON'T GO YET.

01:00:04.824 --> 01:00:07.828
[ Horn Honking ]

01:00:09.328 --> 01:00:11.330
NEED ANY HELP?

01:00:11.330 --> 01:00:13.332
WE'RE ALL RIGHT!

01:00:19.338 --> 01:00:21.340
LOOK--
[ Sniffles ]

01:00:21.340 --> 01:00:23.343
[ Sighs ]

01:00:23.343 --> 01:00:25.344
I DIDN'T MEAN
WHAT I SAID.

01:00:26.345 --> 01:00:29.850
I'M SORRY.
I REALLY AM.

01:00:33.352 --> 01:00:34.854
COME HERE,
I'LL SHOW YOU.

01:00:44.363 --> 01:00:48.367
[ Jacob ]
WE STAYED FOR
A WHILE LONGER.

01:00:48.367 --> 01:00:51.370
[ Sighs ]
WE SORT OF MADE UP AND...

01:00:51.370 --> 01:00:53.373
IT WAS NICE, BUT...

01:00:54.874 --> 01:00:58.377
BY NOW WE WERE BOTH
SO TIRED,

01:00:58.878 --> 01:01:00.380
SO WIPED OUT.

01:01:00.881 --> 01:01:04.383
IT WAS BEGINNING TO GET LATE,
SO I FINALLY STARTED UP THE CAR.
[ Engine Revving ]

01:01:08.889 --> 01:01:10.890
AND THAT WAS THAT.

01:01:14.894 --> 01:01:17.897
TRIED ROCKING IT,
PUSHING IT.
[ Door Closes ]

01:01:17.897 --> 01:01:22.902
FIRST ME, THEN BOTH OF US.
WE EVEN TRIED PUTTING
FLOOR MATS UNDER THE WHEELS.

01:01:22.902 --> 01:01:25.905
WE JUST ENDED UP
DIGGING OURSELVES IN DEEPER.

01:01:25.905 --> 01:01:28.908
SO FINALLY SHE SAYS,
"GET THE JACK.

01:01:28.908 --> 01:01:31.912
PACK SOME SNOW
UNDER THE RUTS
AND JACK IT UP."

01:01:31.912 --> 01:01:35.414
- AND THAT DIDN'T EVEN WORK.
- THIS IS THE REASON
I CAN'T BE WITH YOU.

01:01:35.414 --> 01:01:39.920
[ Jacob ] NOW WE'RE BOTH
REALLY PISSED OFF AGAIN.
YOU LET SHIT LIKE THIS HAPPEN.

01:01:39.920 --> 01:01:41.921
JUST SHUT UP,
ALL RIGHT?

01:01:41.921 --> 01:01:45.424
IF I WERE WITH KEVIN OR MATT,
I'D BE HOME BY NOW.
WHY ARE YOU SUCH A--

01:01:45.925 --> 01:01:49.428
- I SAID, SHUT UP,
ALL RIGHT?
- [ Sighs ] RICH KID.

01:01:49.428 --> 01:01:52.932
- FUCKIN' PUSSY.
PUSSY RICH--
- I SAID, SHUT UP!

01:01:55.434 --> 01:01:56.936
I DID IT.

01:02:00.940 --> 01:02:02.442
I SLAPPED HER.

01:02:05.444 --> 01:02:06.946
I JUST LOST IT.

01:02:17.958 --> 01:02:20.960
[ Sighs ]
DO I HAVE TO DO THIS?
PLEASE?

01:02:21.460 --> 01:02:24.464
YES. YOU HAVE TO.

01:02:27.967 --> 01:02:29.468
SHE STILL HAD
THE CROWBAR.

01:02:29.969 --> 01:02:31.470
YOU--
[ Grunting ]

01:02:40.480 --> 01:02:44.483
SHE JUST MISSED ME
BY ONE INCH, I SWEAR.
JUST ONE INCH.

01:02:46.986 --> 01:02:50.489
[ Both Grunting ]

01:02:53.993 --> 01:02:55.996
OHH!

01:02:56.495 --> 01:02:57.997
[ Metal Clanks ]

01:02:58.497 --> 01:02:59.999
[ Panting ]

01:03:04.503 --> 01:03:07.506
JUST THAT ONE WORD--
MURDER.

01:03:07.506 --> 01:03:10.510
THAT SOUNDS SO IMPOSSIBLE
TO IMAGINE.

01:03:14.513 --> 01:03:17.516
IT WASN'T EVEN SOMETHING
I WAS TRYING TO DO.

01:03:17.516 --> 01:03:20.519
IT--
IT WASN'T EVEN ME.

01:03:22.021 --> 01:03:26.026
IF I HAD
JUST MISSED HER
BY ONE INCH--

01:03:27.526 --> 01:03:29.028
ONE INCH,
JUST LIKE,

01:03:31.030 --> 01:03:33.032
LIKE SHE DID ME--

01:03:34.034 --> 01:03:36.535
[ Sighs ]
MY BIGGEST PROBLEM
WOULD BE,

01:03:36.535 --> 01:03:40.539
DO I SAY HELLO TO HER
WHEN I SEE HER
IN THE SCHOOL HALL.

01:03:51.550 --> 01:03:53.552
DARLING.

01:03:55.554 --> 01:03:57.057
THANKS.

01:03:58.557 --> 01:04:00.559
MMM.

01:04:00.559 --> 01:04:02.561
NOW WE KNOW.

01:04:02.561 --> 01:04:05.564
AT LEAST THAT'S
SOMETHING, BEN.

01:04:05.564 --> 01:04:10.069
IF HE TELLS IT THAT WAY
IN COURT, THE SAME WAY
HE TOLD IT TO US--

01:04:10.069 --> 01:04:14.073
HE WOULDN'T BE TELLING IT
TO PEOPLE WHO LOVE HIM.
NO, THEY'LL BELIEVE HIM.

01:04:14.073 --> 01:04:17.076
THEY'LL SEE THAT IT WAS
JUST AN ACCIDENT.

01:04:18.077 --> 01:04:21.080
ARE YOU PREPARED
TO BET HIS FREEDOM
ON THAT?

01:04:22.581 --> 01:04:26.085
WHAT'S THE ANSWER, THEN?
OF COURSE HE HAS TO TELL THEM.

01:04:28.087 --> 01:04:31.090
BEN, OF COURSE
HE HAS TO TELL THEM.

01:04:31.090 --> 01:04:33.592
LET HIM TELL PANOS
FIRST, OKAY?

01:04:33.592 --> 01:04:37.096
WE'RE NOT LAWYERS, CAROLYN.
THERE MIGHT BE A CERTAIN WAY
THIS SHOULD BE,

01:04:37.096 --> 01:04:39.098
I DON'T KNOW,
PRESENTED.

01:04:40.099 --> 01:04:43.103
I'LL TAKE HIM IN
TOMORROW MORNING.
OKAY?

01:05:22.675 --> 01:05:25.678
- YOU'RE UP PRETTY EARLY.
- [ Gasps ]

01:05:25.678 --> 01:05:27.680
I WASN'T GOING
ANYWHERE.

01:05:31.684 --> 01:05:34.186
THEY KEPT THE CAR.

01:05:39.692 --> 01:05:41.694
BUT IT'S CLEAN.

01:05:41.694 --> 01:05:43.697
AT LEAST
I HOPE TO GOD.

01:05:54.707 --> 01:05:58.712
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
MOM SAID SOMETHING TOO,
LAST NIGHT.

01:05:58.712 --> 01:06:03.215
OH, JAKE,
IT'S NOT IMPORTANT,
ALL THAT STUFF.

01:06:04.216 --> 01:06:07.219
TRUST ME.
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM ANYMORE.

01:06:07.219 --> 01:06:11.223
[ Sighs ]
DAD, YOU COULD
GO TO JAIL TOO.

01:06:11.223 --> 01:06:14.227
IF THEY HAVE
TO TAKE ONE OF US,
IT'S BETTER IT'S ME.

01:06:14.227 --> 01:06:15.728
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

01:06:17.730 --> 01:06:20.232
JACOB, LISTEN TO ME.

01:06:20.733 --> 01:06:24.737
THAT NIGHT WHEN I CAME OUT HERE
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW WHAT
I WAS DOING-- PURE INSTINCT.

01:06:26.238 --> 01:06:29.241
BUT MAYBE I BOUGHT US
A CHANCE.

01:06:29.241 --> 01:06:33.245
THEY'VE GOT NO MURDER WEAPON,
NO PHYSICAL EVIDENCE,
NO WITNESSES.

01:06:34.747 --> 01:06:36.749
AND WE NEVER HEARD
YOUR CONFESSION.

01:06:36.749 --> 01:06:38.751
YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

01:06:38.751 --> 01:06:42.254
YOU NEVER SAID IT
AND WE NEVER HEARD IT.

01:06:44.758 --> 01:06:48.260
JAKE, YOU'RE NOT
REQUIRED TO TESTIFY
AGAINST YOURSELF.

01:06:48.260 --> 01:06:50.262
NOW, THAT'S FAIR.
THAT'S LEGAL.

01:06:50.262 --> 01:06:52.766
THAT'S HOW
THE SYSTEM WORKS.

01:06:53.766 --> 01:06:57.269
SO, IF WE ALL
JUST KEEP QUIET,

01:06:57.269 --> 01:06:59.271
MAYBE THEY'VE GOT
NO CASE.

01:06:59.271 --> 01:07:01.774
MAYBE--

01:07:01.774 --> 01:07:05.778
MAYBE YOU'LL WALK AWAY
FROM THIS WITH SOME KIND OF
A LIFE STILL AHEAD OF YOU.

01:07:05.778 --> 01:07:07.781
YEAH, BUT THERE ARE
WITNESSES.

01:07:07.781 --> 01:07:11.283
PEOPLE SAW US PARKED THERE.
YOU'RE NOT DENYING
YOU WERE THERE.

01:07:11.283 --> 01:07:13.786
YOU WERE STUCK
IN THE SNOW, RIGHT?

01:07:13.786 --> 01:07:16.789
YOU HAD THAT ARGUMENT
AND YOU WALKED AWAY MAD,

01:07:16.789 --> 01:07:19.291
LEFT HER WITH
THE CAR AND THE KEYS.

01:07:19.291 --> 01:07:23.296
SO YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE HELL HAPPENED WHEN SHE
WAS ALONE, AND NEITHER DO WE.

01:07:23.296 --> 01:07:26.799
- WAIT A MINUTE.
BUT THE CAR WAS HERE.
- YOU RECONSIDERED.

01:07:26.799 --> 01:07:29.802
YOU CAME BACK
AND YOU FOUND HER.

01:07:29.802 --> 01:07:31.804
YOU JUST PANICKED.

01:07:31.804 --> 01:07:35.307
ISN'T THAT POSSIBLE?
BECAUSE YOU KNEW
YOU'D BE A SUSPECT.

01:07:35.307 --> 01:07:38.811
DROVE BACK HERE,
STILL IN A STATE OF SHOCK,
AND TOOK OFF FOR BOSTON.

01:07:38.811 --> 01:07:40.813
FOOLISH, YES.

01:07:40.813 --> 01:07:42.815
BUT NOT MURDER.

01:07:45.317 --> 01:07:47.820
I WISH THERE WAS
SOME OTHER WAY.

01:07:47.820 --> 01:07:51.824
I STAYED UP ALL NIGHT
WRACKING MY BRAINS-- ANY
OTHER WAY THAT MIGHT BE SAFE.

01:07:58.330 --> 01:08:00.833
IF I JUST TOLD THE TRUTH--

01:08:01.334 --> 01:08:05.838
THE FACT THAT YOU RAN AWAY,
NEVER WENT FOR HELP,
NEVER CAME FORWARD AT ALL--

01:08:05.838 --> 01:08:08.841
JAKE, HOW'S THAT
GONNA LOOK?

01:08:10.843 --> 01:08:14.346
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
CONVINCE A JURY.
THAT'S UP TO PANOS.

01:08:14.346 --> 01:08:17.850
AND LET THE PROSECUTION
TAKE THEIR SHOTS.

01:08:17.850 --> 01:08:21.353
ALL I'M SAYING IS,
LET'S JUST...

01:08:21.854 --> 01:08:23.856
NOT MAKE THEIR CASE
FOR THEM.

01:08:26.859 --> 01:08:31.363
SO I THOUGHT--
I FIGURED SINCE THE POLICE
WERE BOUND TO SUSPECT ME,

01:08:31.363 --> 01:08:34.366
THEY'D ALSO BE LOOKING
FOR THE CAR, SO...

01:08:35.868 --> 01:08:37.870
I THOUGHT
I'D BETTER HITCHHIKE.

01:08:40.372 --> 01:08:42.374
[ Clears Throat ]

01:08:44.877 --> 01:08:50.381
[ Sighs ]
I-I KNOW THAT WAS REALLY
STUPID AND DUMB OF ME, BUT--

01:08:50.381 --> 01:08:52.384
[ Sighs ]

01:08:53.886 --> 01:08:58.390
YOU KNOW, ALL OF IT
IS JUST A BLUR,
MR. DEMERIS.

01:08:58.390 --> 01:09:01.894
EVERYTHING
AFTER I WALKED BACK
AND FOUND HER THERE.

01:09:05.898 --> 01:09:07.899
[ Tape Recorder
Clicks Off ]

01:09:10.402 --> 01:09:14.907
WELL, JACOB, WHAT IF I SAID
IT SEEMED PRETTY CLEAR TO ME
THAT YOU DID IT?

01:09:14.907 --> 01:09:18.410
YOU HIT HER ON THE HEAD
WITH SOMETHING,
THEN YOU JUST TOOK OFF.

01:09:18.410 --> 01:09:20.912
- BUT I DIDN'T!
- NO, NO, NO.

01:09:20.912 --> 01:09:25.917
NO, I'M THE PROSECUTION NOW,
AND YOU'RE THE GUY
WHO SMASHED HER UP.

01:09:25.917 --> 01:09:29.921
HOW YOU GONNA PROVE TO ME
YOU DIDN'T DO IT?

01:09:32.925 --> 01:09:34.926
WELL, I--
NO, NO, NO, NO.

01:09:35.928 --> 01:09:37.930
YOU DON'T ANSWER THAT.

01:09:37.930 --> 01:09:41.934
NOW, REMEMBER, JACOB,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
ANSWER THAT QUESTION.

01:09:41.934 --> 01:09:45.437
THEYHAVE TO ANSWER IT.
THEY HAVE TO PROVE
SOMETHING ONYOU.

01:09:45.437 --> 01:09:48.439
YOU DO NOT HAVE TO PROVE
THE OPPOSITE.

01:09:50.943 --> 01:09:52.944
SO?
HOW DOES IT LOOK?

01:09:53.444 --> 01:09:57.950
WELL, THE GRAND JURY SITS
NEXT MONDAY, BUT WE'VE STILL
GOT A HELL OF A LOT TO PREPARE.

01:09:57.950 --> 01:10:00.953
- YOU MEAN THE TRIAL
STARTS MONDAY?
- NO, NO, NO.

01:10:00.953 --> 01:10:02.955
IT'S NOT A TRIAL.
NOT YET.

01:10:02.955 --> 01:10:07.960
THE GRAND JURY WEIGHS THE FACTS,
THEN DECIDES WHETHER THERE'S
ENOUGH EVIDENCE TO INDICT YOU.

01:10:07.960 --> 01:10:11.964
NOW, IF YOU'RE VERY,
VERY LUCKY, YOU MAY NOT
EVEN GO TO TRIAL.

01:10:11.964 --> 01:10:16.468
BUT I'LL HAVE A BETTER IDEA
ONCE I SEE THE FINAL
WITNESS LIST AND FORENSICS.

01:10:18.970 --> 01:10:20.973
THANKS.

01:10:20.973 --> 01:10:23.475
OKAY.
THANKS.
SEE YA.

01:10:23.475 --> 01:10:27.479
OH, JAKE. I'M SORRY.
I'M A LITTLE SLOW
SOMETIMES.

01:10:27.479 --> 01:10:30.482
I'M JUST CURIOUS.
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

01:10:30.482 --> 01:10:33.485
WHAT WERE THE TWO OF YOU
FIGHTING ABOUT?

01:10:33.485 --> 01:10:35.988
I-I MEAN,
W-WHAT GOT YOU SO MAD?

01:10:35.988 --> 01:10:38.991
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I LET THIS GO.

01:10:38.991 --> 01:10:40.993
SHE WAS PREGNANT,
FOR ONE THING.

01:10:42.494 --> 01:10:46.498
- I THINK YOU'D BETTER
SIT DOWN AGAIN, KIDDO.
- COME ON, SON.

01:10:52.004 --> 01:10:56.008
IT WAS SOMEBODY ELSE'S.
AT LEAST SHE SAID IT WAS.

01:10:58.010 --> 01:11:00.012
WHAT?
THIS IS GOOD?

01:11:00.012 --> 01:11:05.017
OH, THIS IS VERY GOOD,
MY FRIEND. THIS IS THE
BEST NEWS I'VE HEARD ALL DAY.

01:11:05.017 --> 01:11:08.520
AND YOU'RE CONVINCED
THAT IT COULDN'T POSSIBLY
HAVE BEEN YOURS?

01:11:09.521 --> 01:11:12.024
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

01:11:12.024 --> 01:11:14.026
YOU MEAN--

01:11:14.026 --> 01:11:16.528
YOU KNOW.
RIGHT. YOU KNOW.

01:11:18.530 --> 01:11:22.034
WELL, YEAH, BUT
WE WERE AL--
WE WERE ALWAYS--

01:11:22.034 --> 01:11:24.536
SAFE.
YOU CAN SAY IT, SON.
YEAH.

01:11:24.536 --> 01:11:27.039
AND SHE SWORE THIS
WAS SOMEBODY ELSE'S.

01:11:27.039 --> 01:11:31.043
GO TO THE MEDICAL EXAMINER,
GET A FULL D.N.A. REPORT.
I'M ALREADY ON IT.

01:11:33.045 --> 01:11:37.049
PANOS, WH-- I DON'T--
WE STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND.

01:11:37.049 --> 01:11:39.551
IT'S CALLED REASONABLE DOUBT,
MR. RYAN.

01:11:39.551 --> 01:11:43.555
SUPPOSE JACOB AND MARTHA
WERE FOLLOWED BY SOMEONE WITH
GOOD REASON TO BE JEALOUS.

01:11:43.555 --> 01:11:46.558
SUPPOSE THE WRONG BOYFRIEND
GOT ARRESTED.

01:11:50.062 --> 01:11:52.064
SO?

01:11:55.067 --> 01:11:57.069
SO WHAT?

01:11:57.069 --> 01:11:59.071
HOW DO YOU THINK
IT WENT?

01:12:01.073 --> 01:12:05.577
DID HE LIKE IT, YOU MEAN,
OR DIDILIKE IT?
LIKE WHAT?

01:12:05.577 --> 01:12:07.579
YOUR STORY.

01:12:07.579 --> 01:12:10.082
WELL, YES, MY STORY,
I GUESS.

01:12:10.082 --> 01:12:12.084
OURSTORY.

01:12:14.586 --> 01:12:17.089
JAKE,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

01:12:17.089 --> 01:12:19.091
[ Signal Blinker
Clicking ]

01:12:38.610 --> 01:12:40.612
WHAT?

01:12:45.117 --> 01:12:47.119
REMEMBER
THAT LAST MORNING?

01:12:49.621 --> 01:12:53.125
THAT ARGUMENT WE HAD?
REMEMBER WHAT YOU SAID
TO ME?

01:12:53.125 --> 01:12:56.628
YOU SAID THAT IT'S TIME
I LEARNED TO PAY MY OWN WAY.

01:12:56.628 --> 01:12:58.630
AND YOU CALLED ME
A HYPOCRITE.

01:13:00.132 --> 01:13:04.636
JAKE, IF YOU'RE NOT
OKAY WITH THIS,
WE CAN GO BACK THERE.

01:13:04.636 --> 01:13:07.639
IT'S STILL
NOT TOO LATE.
[ Sighs ]
OH, MAN.

01:13:09.141 --> 01:13:12.644
YOU SURE THIS IS
THE BEST THING TO DO?

01:13:12.644 --> 01:13:16.148
I HAVEN'T BEEN SURE
OF ANYTHING IN MY LIFE
SINCE FEBRUARY 12,

01:13:16.148 --> 01:13:19.651
BUT IT'S WHAT
WE'VE GOT, SON;
IT'S WHAT WE'RE DOWN TO.

01:13:19.651 --> 01:13:22.153
ALL I'M PROPOSING IS
WE SAVE YOUR LIFE FIRST.

01:13:22.153 --> 01:13:24.656
LATER ON WE CAN WORRY
ABOUT YOUR SOUL.

01:13:25.157 --> 01:13:27.659
IS THAT BEING A HYPOCRITE?
I DON'T KNOW.

01:13:28.160 --> 01:13:30.662
BUT THE WORST THING
YOU CAN BE CALLED
IN THIS WORLD...

01:13:31.163 --> 01:13:33.665
IS SOMEONE WHO DIDN'T
STAND UP FOR HIS FAMILY.

01:13:33.665 --> 01:13:36.168
I--

01:13:36.168 --> 01:13:38.170
[ Sighs ]

01:13:38.170 --> 01:13:41.673
I REALLY AM GRATEFUL
FOR EVERYTHING YOU'RE
TRYING TO DO FOR ME.

01:13:41.673 --> 01:13:43.675
I--

01:13:45.676 --> 01:13:48.680
DAD, IAMGRATEFUL,
OKAY?

01:13:49.681 --> 01:13:51.683
I REALLY MEAN IT.

01:13:53.184 --> 01:13:54.686
COME ON.

01:13:57.689 --> 01:14:01.693
WITHOUT A WORD, BEN?
NOT ONE WORD?

01:14:01.693 --> 01:14:04.196
IT'S JACOB'S CHOICE,
JACOB'S LIFE.

01:14:06.698 --> 01:14:09.201
AND YOU HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

01:14:09.201 --> 01:14:11.203
WE DISCUSSED
HIS OPTIONS, YEAH.

01:14:11.203 --> 01:14:13.205
"OPTIONS"?

01:14:14.206 --> 01:14:16.207
BEN, HE'S YOUR BOY.

01:14:16.207 --> 01:14:19.711
HE'S SCARED AND AFRAID
AND HE WOULD DO ANYTHING
RIGHT NOW,

01:14:19.711 --> 01:14:23.214
HE WOULD SAY ANYTHING,
IF HE THOUGHT HE COULD
WIN BACK YOUR APPROVAL.

01:14:23.214 --> 01:14:25.217
HE NEVER LOST IT.

01:14:25.217 --> 01:14:29.221
AND IF YOU DON'T KNOW HE
DESERVES YOURS TOO, THEN YOU'VE
GOT A SERIOUS GODDAMN PROBLEM.

01:14:29.221 --> 01:14:31.222
HOW DARE YOU?
HOW DARE YOU?

01:14:31.222 --> 01:14:35.727
- IT'S DONE, IT'S TAKEN CARE OF.
- JUST LIKE YOU TOOK CARE
OF THE EVIDENCE.

01:14:35.727 --> 01:14:38.230
[ Ben ] THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU NEVER EVEN HAD TO
DIRTY YOUR PRECIOUS HANDS.

01:14:38.230 --> 01:14:40.732
[ Carolyn ]
TRIM A LITTLE HERE,
ADD A LITTLE THERE.

01:14:40.732 --> 01:14:44.736
HOW COULD I FORGET HOW CLEVER
YOU ARE AT MAKING THINGS?
ONE OF US HAD TO DO SOMETHING.

01:14:44.736 --> 01:14:47.739
DO YOU THINK YOU'VE MADE IT
EASIER ON HIM NOW?

01:14:47.739 --> 01:14:50.742
DO YOU NOT SEE THAT YOU
HAVE TIED HIS HANDS?

01:14:51.243 --> 01:14:55.247
NOW HE HAS YOU TO DEFEND
AS WELL AS HIMSELF.

01:14:55.747 --> 01:14:57.249
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
WHAT?

01:14:57.749 --> 01:15:00.752
THAT HE SHOULD PAY
WITH THE NEXT 20 YEARS,
30 YEARS OF HIS LIFE...

01:15:01.252 --> 01:15:02.754
FOR ONE MISTAKE,
FOR ONE MOMENT?

01:15:03.255 --> 01:15:06.758
THAT HE SHOULD COME OUT
OF PRISON A MIDDLE-AGED MAN?

01:15:07.259 --> 01:15:09.760
WHO DOES THAT BENEFIT?
WHO?

01:15:11.763 --> 01:15:13.265
OH, LOVE.

01:15:13.765 --> 01:15:16.767
SOONER OR LATER SOMEBODY'S
GONNA HAVE TO BE FORGIVEN--

01:15:16.767 --> 01:15:20.772
HIM FOR WHAT HE DID, OR US
BECAUSE WE DID NOTHING WHEN
WE HAD A CHANCE TO SAVE HIM.

01:15:25.777 --> 01:15:27.779
WOULDN'T YOU RATHER
FORGIVE HIM?

01:15:35.787 --> 01:15:38.790
[ Whispers ]
HEY... JUDE.

01:15:44.796 --> 01:15:46.798
[ Door Closes ]

01:15:52.804 --> 01:15:54.805
[ People Murmuring,
Chattering ]

01:16:08.320 --> 01:16:10.321
GOOD NEWS.

01:16:10.321 --> 01:16:14.826
OKAY, I STOPPED AT THE LAB
ON THE WAY UP HERE.

01:16:14.826 --> 01:16:18.829
NOW, THEY HAD THE M.E.'S
FETAL TISSUE ANALYSIS...

01:16:18.829 --> 01:16:22.834
AND THEY HAVE
THAT BLOOD SAMPLE THAT
WE SUBMITTED FROM JACOB.

01:16:22.834 --> 01:16:25.336
OKAY, THIS GETS
PRETTY TECHNICAL, BUT--

01:16:25.336 --> 01:16:27.339
JACOB WASN'T
THE FATHER.

01:16:27.339 --> 01:16:29.341
BINGO.

01:16:29.341 --> 01:16:32.344
OH, MAN, LISTEN TO ME,
TELLING A DOCTOR
WHAT'S TECHNICAL.

01:16:32.344 --> 01:16:34.846
BUT THIS WORKS
BOTH WAYS, DOESN'T IT?

01:16:34.846 --> 01:16:38.350
I MEAN, THEY COULD SAY
HE WAS JEALOUS.
THIS GIVES HIM A MOTIVE.

01:16:38.350 --> 01:16:41.852
THIS LETS US
GO AFTER THE GIRL,
ATTACK HER CHARACTER.

01:16:41.852 --> 01:16:45.357
MARTHA TAVERNER JUST BLEW
50 SYMPATHY POINTS.

01:16:45.357 --> 01:16:48.859
LOOK AT IT THIS WAY:
THIS INTRODUCES DOUBT.

01:16:48.859 --> 01:16:51.863
AND DOUBT, KIDDO,
IS OUR VERY BEST FRIEND.

01:16:51.863 --> 01:16:54.866
- [ Door Opens ]
- MRS. RYAN?

01:16:54.866 --> 01:16:57.369
[ Ben Shouting ]
GET AWAY FROM ME!
EXCUSE ME. MRS. RYAN.

01:16:57.369 --> 01:17:00.372
WHAT HAPPENED?
WE'LL SEE YOU DAY AFTER
TOMORROW AT 10:00.

01:17:00.372 --> 01:17:02.374
YES, THAT'S FINE.
[ Reporters Shouting ]

01:17:02.874 --> 01:17:06.378
BENNY? BEN?
SCREW THEM! FORGET
THE WHOLE BUNCH OF THEM!

01:17:06.378 --> 01:17:09.381
I DIDN'T TESTIFY
AND I WON'T TESTIFY!

01:17:09.381 --> 01:17:13.385
SO YOU CAN PRINT
ANY DAMN THING YOU WANT TO!
HERE, GET THIS ONE!

01:17:13.385 --> 01:17:16.888
YOU DIDN'T TESTIFY?
THERE'S GOTTA BE SOME
PROTECTION, SOME IMMUNITY,

01:17:16.888 --> 01:17:20.892
SOME KIND OF PRIVILEGE SO THEY
CAN'T TRY TO MAKE YOU SNITCH
ON YOUR OWN FLESH AND BLOOD.

01:17:20.892 --> 01:17:24.396
WHY DON'T YOU WRITE THAT?
THERE'S SUCH A THING AS
THE FIFTH AMENDMENT.

01:17:24.396 --> 01:17:26.897
ASK MY LAWYER!
[ Reporter Shouting ]
WHAT ARE YOU HIDING?

01:17:27.398 --> 01:17:30.402
WEREN'T YOU
LISTENING TO ME?

01:17:30.402 --> 01:17:34.405
I TOLD YOU IF YOU HAD ANYTHING
TO ASK, COME OUT AND ASK ME!
I DIDN'T HAVE ANY QUESTIONS.

01:17:34.405 --> 01:17:37.909
FIND ME SOME PRIVILEGE.
"FIND ME SOME PRIVILEGE."
WHAT, MAKE SOMETHING UP?

01:17:37.909 --> 01:17:40.912
[ Reporters Murmuring ]
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS PARENT-CHILD IMMUNITY.

01:17:40.912 --> 01:17:43.915
THERE OUGHTA BE.
YOU KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE ASKING FOR?

01:17:43.915 --> 01:17:46.918
YOU'RE ASKING TO GO
TO JAIL FOR CONTEMPT,
FOR STARTERS.

01:17:46.918 --> 01:17:50.421
YOU'RE ASKING ME TO GO
TO JAIL TOO, AND I'M NOT
DOING ANY SUCH THING FOR YOU.

01:17:50.421 --> 01:17:52.424
WHAT DID HE MEAN
BY "PRIVILEGE"?

01:17:53.925 --> 01:17:56.927
YOU'RE ACTING
AS IF WE'VE GOT SOMETHING
TO HIDE ABOUT JACOB.

01:17:56.927 --> 01:18:01.433
THEY TWISTED EVERY WORD I SAID,
TRIED TO TRICK ME INTO SOME
KIND OF CONFLICTING EVIDENCE.

01:18:01.433 --> 01:18:05.436
I WON'T PLAY THAT GAME.
I TOLD THEM SO. I GAVE THEM
A STATEMENT OF PRINCIPLE.

01:18:05.436 --> 01:18:08.940
AND WHAT WAS THAT PRINCIPLE?
I THINK I MISSED THAT PART.
I DON'T BARGAIN FOR MY SON.

01:18:08.940 --> 01:18:12.443
AND I WON'T HELP THEM
TO CONVICT HIM.
JESUS, BEN!

01:18:12.443 --> 01:18:15.947
I WON'T TESTIFY, PANOS.
NOT TODAY, NOT EVER.

01:18:15.947 --> 01:18:18.950
IF I HAVE TO GO TO JAIL,
SO BE IT.

01:18:18.950 --> 01:18:22.954
AND IF THERE WAS ANY MORE
I COULD DO, YOU'D BETTER
BELIEVE I'D DO THAT TOO.

01:18:22.954 --> 01:18:24.956
[ Reporters Shouting ]

01:18:24.956 --> 01:18:26.958
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:18:35.265 --> 01:18:37.135
[ Knock On Door ]

01:18:37.135 --> 01:18:40.138
OH. GIVE ME A MINUTE,
BEN, PLEASE.

01:18:43.140 --> 01:18:45.143
MOM, CAN I
TALK TO YOU?

01:18:47.645 --> 01:18:49.647
MM-HMM.

01:18:54.152 --> 01:18:56.654
MOM, THEY'RE LYING.

01:18:56.654 --> 01:19:00.158
THEY'RE COMPLETELY CHANGING
THE TRUTH OF WHAT HAPPENED.

01:19:00.158 --> 01:19:03.161
HOW CAN YOU
LET THEM DO THAT?

01:19:04.162 --> 01:19:08.166
WELL, PEOPLE DON'T GO
TO COURT NECESSARILY...

01:19:08.166 --> 01:19:11.169
TO TELL THE TRUTH ABOUT
EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED.

01:19:12.670 --> 01:19:16.674
THEY, UM-- THEY GO
TO DEFEND THEMSELVES
THE BEST WAY THEY CAN.

01:19:17.175 --> 01:19:20.178
BUT YOU HEARD JACOB
AND YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

01:19:21.678 --> 01:19:24.682
ARE YOU JUST GONNA DO
WHAT DADDY SAYS?

01:19:24.682 --> 01:19:26.684
[ Sighs ]
JUDE.

01:19:26.684 --> 01:19:31.189
DIDN'T YOU EVER LEARN
SOMETHING ABOUT A FRIEND
OF YOURS, SOME SECRET,

01:19:31.189 --> 01:19:36.193
BUT YOU KNEW IF YOU TOLD HER
IT WOULD JUST HURT HER FEELINGS,
SO YOU DIDN'T TELL?

01:19:36.693 --> 01:19:39.197
I MEAN, THAT'S NOT--

01:19:39.197 --> 01:19:41.199
THAT'S NOT LYING EXACTLY.

01:19:41.199 --> 01:19:44.201
IT'S-- YOU JUST DIDN'T
VOLUNTEER SOMETHING.

01:19:44.201 --> 01:19:46.204
JUST BECAUSE
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO,

01:19:46.204 --> 01:19:50.708
JUST BECAUSE THEY MIGHT
GET AWAY WITH IT, DOES THAT
MEAN YOU HAVE TO LIE?

01:19:52.209 --> 01:19:54.212
SOMETIMES-- YOU'RE JUST--
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG...

01:19:54.212 --> 01:19:56.214
TO UNDERSTAND SOME THINGS,
THAT'S ALL.

01:19:56.214 --> 01:20:00.217
I'M JUST BEGINNING TO LEARN
SOME OF THEM MYSELF.

01:20:00.217 --> 01:20:03.221
SOMEDAY, DARLING,
YOU MIGHT...
DON'T TELL ME "SOMEDAY"!

01:20:03.221 --> 01:20:06.723
UNDERSTAND WHAT DADDY--
I CAN'T STAND IT
WHEN YOU SAY "SOMEDAY"!

01:20:06.723 --> 01:20:09.227
THIS IS HAPPENING
TO ME RIGHT NOW.

01:20:09.227 --> 01:20:12.230
[ Judith ]
YOU LET DADDY CONVINCE YOU.

01:20:12.230 --> 01:20:15.232
IT'S DISGUSTING.

01:20:15.232 --> 01:20:19.237
NOBODY EVEN CARES
WHAT I THINK; I'M JUST
A STUPID LITTLE KID.

01:20:20.738 --> 01:20:24.242
NOBODY EVEN THINKS THAT
I COULD GO AND TELL.

01:20:24.242 --> 01:20:26.244
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"TELL"?

01:20:26.244 --> 01:20:28.746
YOU FIGURE IT OUT!
JUDITH.

01:20:28.746 --> 01:20:31.749
[ Door Slams ]
[ Footsteps
Descending Stairs ]

01:20:34.752 --> 01:20:38.255
CAROLYN,
YOU ASLEEP?

01:20:38.255 --> 01:20:40.258
MM-MMM.

01:20:41.759 --> 01:20:44.761
ABRAHAM AND ISAAC.
REMEMBER THAT STORY?

01:20:47.265 --> 01:20:49.267
GOD SAYS TO ABRAHAM,

01:20:49.767 --> 01:20:51.769
"PROVE YOUR FAITH.

01:20:51.769 --> 01:20:55.273
"TAKE ISAAC,
YOUR BELOVED SON,
AND SACRIFICE HIM.

01:20:57.275 --> 01:20:59.277
"WHY?
BECAUSE I'M GOD.

01:20:59.277 --> 01:21:01.278
BECAUSE I SAY SO."

01:21:02.280 --> 01:21:04.282
AND ABRAHAM IS WILLING.

01:21:04.282 --> 01:21:06.784
HE'S VERY SAD,
BUT HE'LL DO IT.

01:21:06.784 --> 01:21:08.785
HE'LL CUT
HIS OWN SON'S THROAT...

01:21:08.785 --> 01:21:10.788
IF THAT'S WHAT GOD
REQUIRES.

01:21:12.290 --> 01:21:14.792
VERY OBEDIENT,
ABRAHAM.

01:21:14.792 --> 01:21:16.793
AND VERY RIGHTEOUS.

01:21:19.297 --> 01:21:23.300
BUT WHEN
THEY TELL THAT STORY
THEY ALWAYS MISS THE POINT.

01:21:25.303 --> 01:21:27.305
WHO'D WANT HIM
FOR A FATHER?

01:21:39.316 --> 01:21:41.319
[ People Chattering
Quietly ]

01:22:02.339 --> 01:22:04.342
GOOD MORNING, CAROLYN.
HI.

01:22:06.344 --> 01:22:10.347
FIRST TIME
YOU'VE DONATED BLOOD?
YES.

01:22:10.347 --> 01:22:12.350
[ Sighs ]

01:22:14.852 --> 01:22:16.853
[ Toilet Flushes ]

01:22:32.369 --> 01:22:34.372
MRS. TAVERNER.

01:22:36.374 --> 01:22:38.376
OH, PLEASE.

01:22:43.881 --> 01:22:47.884
THIS HAS BEEN,
FOR ME, FOR ALL OF US--
IT'S THE HARDEST--

01:22:47.884 --> 01:22:52.390
I'VE JUST-- I'VE SPENT
A THOUSAND HOURS NOT SLEEPING,

01:22:52.390 --> 01:22:55.892
THINKING ABOUT... MARTHA.

01:22:56.393 --> 01:22:59.397
AND I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW HOW SORRY I AM.

01:22:59.397 --> 01:23:02.899
I AM SO SORRY.

01:23:05.903 --> 01:23:08.406
I KNOW IT WON'T
CHANGE ANYTHING, BUT--

01:23:08.906 --> 01:23:11.408
[ Sighs ]
OH, GOD, IF YOU COULD--

01:23:11.908 --> 01:23:13.911
WHAT?
IF I COULD WHAT?

01:23:13.911 --> 01:23:16.914
IF YOU COULD SOMEHOW...

01:23:16.914 --> 01:23:20.918
LOOK AT US AS HUMAN--
AS A FAMILY, I MEAN.

01:23:20.918 --> 01:23:24.422
JUST AS A FAMILY
THAT'S ALSO SO HELPLESS.

01:23:25.922 --> 01:23:30.928
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
TO BE HELPLESS ABOUT?
YOU TELL ME THAT.

01:23:30.928 --> 01:23:33.930
SHE WAS ALIVE IN THE MORNING
WHEN I SAID GOOD-BYE TO HER.

01:23:33.930 --> 01:23:37.435
YOU'RE A DOCTOR.
YOU THINK ABOUT THIS,
WHERE SHE IS NOW.

01:23:37.435 --> 01:23:39.937
AND NOTHING YOU SAY
IS GONNA GET ANY PITY
OUT OF ME.

01:23:39.937 --> 01:23:42.939
OH, I'M NOT ASKING
FOR YOUR PITY.

01:23:42.939 --> 01:23:46.944
I'M-- I'M JUST--
YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET HIM OFF.

01:23:46.944 --> 01:23:49.446
WITH YOUR BIG SHOT LAWYER
AND ALL YOUR MONEY.

01:23:49.446 --> 01:23:52.950
HE'S FREE TO WALK THE STREETS
RIGHT NOW, AND YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET HIM OFF.

01:23:52.950 --> 01:23:56.953
PEOPLE LIKE YOU THINK
THEY OWN THE WORLD.

01:23:56.953 --> 01:23:59.457
[ People Chattering ]

01:24:13.470 --> 01:24:15.973
[ Glass Breaking ]

01:24:15.973 --> 01:24:17.975
JESUS.

01:24:25.483 --> 01:24:27.484
- STAY INSIDE.
CALL THE POLICE.
- [ Carolyn ] NO, BEN!

01:24:27.984 --> 01:24:29.987
- [ Jacob ] DAD, DON'T!
- [ Ben ] HEY!

01:24:30.488 --> 01:24:34.491
- COME HERE, YOU BASTARD!
- [ Man ] I DID IT.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

01:24:34.991 --> 01:24:36.994
- BEN!
- [ Man Grunts ]

01:24:42.999 --> 01:24:46.003
HEY! HEY, YOU!
COME ON!
JAKE! JAKE!

01:24:46.003 --> 01:24:49.005
PLEASE!
LET'S GO!
COME ON!

01:24:49.506 --> 01:24:53.010
[ Men Yelling,
Whooping ]

01:25:00.017 --> 01:25:03.020
MOM!
GOD!

01:25:03.020 --> 01:25:05.021
GODDAMN IT!

01:25:05.021 --> 01:25:07.023
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

01:25:07.023 --> 01:25:11.528
HERE!
THIS IS YOUR FAULT!
BOTH OF YOURS!

01:25:11.528 --> 01:25:14.531
YOU'VE TURNED US ALL
INTO FREAKS!
SHUT UP, ALL RIGHT?

01:25:14.531 --> 01:25:17.535
I WISH YOU'D NEVER COME BACK.
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST STAY AWAY?

01:25:19.036 --> 01:25:21.538
I HATE YOU!
I HATE YOU!

01:25:21.538 --> 01:25:24.041
OHH!
[ Ben ]
IT'S OKAY, JAKE.

01:25:24.041 --> 01:25:26.043
[ Yells ]

01:25:26.043 --> 01:25:28.044
AAAH! GOD!

01:25:28.044 --> 01:25:30.046
HELP!
[ Carolyn ]
JACOB!

01:25:30.046 --> 01:25:33.050
[ Ben ]
GET DOWN!
[ Jacob Whimpering ]

01:25:33.551 --> 01:25:36.052
[ Crying ]
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

01:25:36.052 --> 01:25:38.556
LET'S GENTLY, GENTLY
GET HIM UP.

01:25:38.556 --> 01:25:41.559
IT'S OKAY.
COME ON, SWEETHEART.
LET ME LOOK. LET ME SEE.

01:25:42.559 --> 01:25:45.061
THAT'S IT, THAT'S IT,
THAT'S IT.

01:25:45.061 --> 01:25:48.065
NO, NO. I CAN'T--
I CAN'T TREAT THIS HERE.
[ Whimpering ]

01:25:48.065 --> 01:25:50.567
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
TAKE HIM TO THE OFFICE.
I'LL COME TOO.

01:25:51.067 --> 01:25:53.069
NO, YOU STAY HERE
WITH JUDITH.
CAROLYN, I--

01:25:53.069 --> 01:25:55.072
PLEASE, BEN.

01:26:01.078 --> 01:26:03.581
THIS WON'T HURT,
I PROMISE.

01:26:09.587 --> 01:26:11.088
THERE YOU GO.

01:26:11.589 --> 01:26:14.090
I'M JUST GONNA
WRAP THIS UP...

01:26:14.090 --> 01:26:17.595
SO WE DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT INFECTION.

01:26:17.595 --> 01:26:20.097
OKAY?

01:26:20.097 --> 01:26:24.101
YOU MAY START TO FEEL
DROWSY NOW FROM THAT SHOT.

01:26:24.101 --> 01:26:27.104
SO IF YOU DO, YOU JUST
PUT YOUR HEAD DOWN.
OKAY, LOVE?

01:26:27.104 --> 01:26:29.105
OKAY.

01:26:33.110 --> 01:26:35.112
MOM?
MM-HMM?

01:26:37.113 --> 01:26:39.115
JUDE IS RIGHT.

01:26:40.618 --> 01:26:44.120
YOU'D ALL BE BETTER OFF
IF I JUST DISAPPEARED.

01:26:44.120 --> 01:26:46.122
MAYBE I STILL SHOULD.

01:26:46.122 --> 01:26:48.125
DON'T EVEN SAY THAT.

01:26:51.127 --> 01:26:54.130
I DON'T MEAN JUST YOU.
I MEAN--

01:26:54.632 --> 01:26:57.134
I MEAN THE WHOLE TOWN.

01:26:57.635 --> 01:26:59.636
I MEAN, THAT'S WHAT
THEY WANT, ISN'T IT?

01:26:59.636 --> 01:27:02.139
NO.

01:27:02.640 --> 01:27:05.643
NO, JAKE, THOSE MEN--

01:27:05.643 --> 01:27:08.645
THOSE MEN TONIGHT
WERE COWARDS.

01:27:09.145 --> 01:27:11.148
IF YOU SAW THEM TOMORROW
IN THEIR SHOPS,

01:27:11.148 --> 01:27:14.651
THEY'D SMILE AND NOD
WHILE THEY GAVE YOU CHANGE.

01:27:17.655 --> 01:27:20.157
I'M THE COWARD.

01:27:20.157 --> 01:27:22.158
I'M THE COWARD.

01:27:26.163 --> 01:27:29.666
I FEEL LIKE I'M BEING
TORN APART, YOU KNOW?

01:27:30.667 --> 01:27:33.671
AND--
[ Sighs ]

01:27:33.671 --> 01:27:36.173
IF I HOLD THIS IN,
I-IT'S LIKE...

01:27:39.676 --> 01:27:41.679
A POISON, YOU KNOW?

01:27:41.679 --> 01:27:44.681
IF I TELL THE TRUTH,
DAD'LL GO TO JAIL TOO.

01:27:44.681 --> 01:27:46.683
HE'LL HATE ME.

01:27:49.186 --> 01:27:51.188
EITHER WAY,
IT'S THE END OF US.

01:27:52.689 --> 01:27:55.692
YOUR DAD'LL NEVER,
NEVER HATE YOU.

01:27:58.696 --> 01:28:00.697
YOUR DAD LOVES YOU...

01:28:02.198 --> 01:28:04.201
SO MUCH, JACOB.

01:28:09.205 --> 01:28:12.209
AND RIGHT OR WRONG,
HE ALWAYS GIVES...

01:28:12.209 --> 01:28:14.211
HIS WHOLE HEART.

01:28:14.211 --> 01:28:16.212
IT CAN BE PRETTY
OVERWHELMING SOMETIMES...

01:28:16.212 --> 01:28:19.216
BECAUSE HE JUST ALWAYS
SEEMS SO SURE.

01:28:21.218 --> 01:28:24.220
BUT YOU DON'T HAVE TO
BE THAT WAY.

01:28:25.221 --> 01:28:27.725
YOU KNOW?

01:28:27.725 --> 01:28:31.227
IT IS POSSIBLE
TO DISAGREE WITH SOMEONE...

01:28:32.729 --> 01:28:34.231
AND STILL LOVE THEM.

01:28:41.739 --> 01:28:45.241
AT A CERTAIN POINT,
WE JUST--

01:28:45.241 --> 01:28:47.744
WE HAVE TO MAKE
OUR OWN DECISIONS.

01:28:49.245 --> 01:28:52.749
YEAH. YEAH, BUT HE
RISKED SO MUCH FOR ME.

01:28:53.249 --> 01:28:55.251
MMM.

01:28:55.251 --> 01:28:57.254
HE DIDN'T EVEN STOP
TO COUNT THE PRICE.

01:28:57.254 --> 01:28:59.256
HE JUST DID IT.

01:29:05.262 --> 01:29:07.264
MOM?
HMM?

01:29:09.265 --> 01:29:11.267
HOW CAN I LET HIM DOWN?

01:29:14.772 --> 01:29:17.273
HOW CAN I
DO THAT TO HIM?

01:29:18.775 --> 01:29:20.778
YEAH.

01:29:22.279 --> 01:29:24.280
HOW CAN YOU?

01:29:46.019 --> 01:29:48.020
[ Whispering ]

01:29:48.020 --> 01:29:50.022
MRS. RYAN?

01:30:03.035 --> 01:30:05.037
DR. RYAN?

01:30:10.543 --> 01:30:14.047
[ People Chattering ]
THERE SHE IS!

01:30:14.548 --> 01:30:16.049
DR. RYAN!
DR. RYAN, DID YOU ALSO
REFUSE TO TESTIFY?

01:30:16.550 --> 01:30:19.552
- HOW'D IT GO, TROUPER?
- I DID IT. I TOLD THEM.

01:30:19.552 --> 01:30:21.555
SEE?
WHAT'D I TELL YOU?

01:30:21.555 --> 01:30:26.058
NO SWEAT.
NO, I MEAN I TOLD THEM
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED.

01:30:26.058 --> 01:30:28.060
WHAT?

01:30:28.060 --> 01:30:30.564
BEN AND JACOB
HAVEN'T BEEN TELLING YOU
THE TRUTH, PANOS.

01:30:31.064 --> 01:30:34.066
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU HAVEN'T KNOWN THAT.
WHOA, WHOA!

01:30:34.567 --> 01:30:36.570
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA DO ABOUT THIS.
YOU COME WITH ME.

01:30:37.070 --> 01:30:38.572
[ Reporter ]
MIGHT WE HAVE
A STATEMENT, PLEASE?

01:30:39.072 --> 01:30:40.573
DR. RYAN!
EXCUSE ME!

01:30:44.578 --> 01:30:46.580
TALK.

01:30:46.580 --> 01:30:48.581
IT'S HARD TO SAY.
THEY'VE BEEN IN THERE
20 MINUTES.

01:30:49.081 --> 01:30:52.085
THERE'S NO STORY HERE.
TWENTY MINUTES!
WHAT ARE THEY TALKING ABOUT?

01:30:54.087 --> 01:30:56.088
OKAY. MY TURN.

01:30:56.088 --> 01:30:58.090
JACOB DOESN'T KNOW,
DOES HE?

01:31:00.594 --> 01:31:02.595
DID YOU AT LEAST
TELL BEN?

01:31:04.597 --> 01:31:07.099
OH, JESUS CHRIST.

01:31:10.102 --> 01:31:13.606
ALL I CAN SAY IS I HOPE HE
DOESN'T HAVE HIS SON'S TEMPER,
BECAUSE I WORRY ABOUT YOU.

01:31:13.606 --> 01:31:16.109
HE DOESN'T HAVE
HIS SON'S TEMPER.

01:31:16.109 --> 01:31:18.611
HIS SON HAS HIS.
THIS WEAPON.

01:31:18.611 --> 01:31:22.114
THIS CAR JACK
THAT YOU SAY KILLED HER.
WHERE IS IT NOW?

01:31:22.114 --> 01:31:26.619
IT'LL NEVER SURFACE,
I PROMISE YOU,
BUT I'M NEVER GOING TO SAY.

01:31:26.619 --> 01:31:28.621
- DID YOU EVER SEE IT?
- MM-MMM.

01:31:30.123 --> 01:31:32.125
WELL, THEN IT'S HEARSAY.

01:31:32.125 --> 01:31:36.128
JUST LIKE THIS SO-CALLED
CONFESSION; IT'S YOUR WORD
AGAINST BEN AND JACOB'S.

01:31:36.128 --> 01:31:39.633
THERE'S STILL NO PROOF.
PANOS, IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

01:31:39.633 --> 01:31:42.134
WHY CAN'T JACOB
JUST TELL THE TRUTH?

01:31:42.134 --> 01:31:45.137
JACOB IS MY CLIENT,
NOT YOU, NOT YOUR HUSBAND.
JACOB.

01:31:45.137 --> 01:31:47.641
AND THERE'S NO WAY
I'M GOING TO PUT HIM
ON THAT WITNESS STAND...

01:31:47.641 --> 01:31:50.142
FOR MARIAN RAYNOR
TO CUT TO PIECES.

01:31:50.142 --> 01:31:53.647
I'M GONNA DEFEND YOUR SON
EVEN IF YOU DON'T.

01:31:56.649 --> 01:31:59.652
EVEN IF IT MEANS
HANGING YOU OUT TO DRY.

01:32:00.653 --> 01:32:03.156
ME?
COLD.

01:32:03.156 --> 01:32:06.158
VINDICTIVE.

01:32:06.158 --> 01:32:10.163
FULL OF CRAZY, PARANOID
FANTASIES ABOUT YOUR SON
AND HIS LOW-CLASS LOVER.

01:32:10.163 --> 01:32:13.666
HONEY, BY THE TIME
I'M DONE WITH YOU,
YOU'LL LOOK LIKE MEDEA.

01:32:13.666 --> 01:32:17.170
PANOS, IF YOU TRY
TO GO ON HIDING THIS--

01:32:17.170 --> 01:32:19.672
IF WE DON'T,
AT SOME POINT, ACCEPT
WHAT ACTUALLY DID HAPPEN--

01:32:20.172 --> 01:32:24.177
WHAT ACTUALLY HAPPENED?
CAROLYN, WHAT'S IT GONNA TAKE
FOR YOU TO GET THIS?

01:32:24.177 --> 01:32:27.680
THEY TELL THEIR VERSION
OF THE STORY; WE TELL OURS.

01:32:28.180 --> 01:32:31.183
- AND THESE 12 PEOPLE
DECIDE THE TRUTH.
- THAT'S NOT THE TRUTH.

01:32:31.183 --> 01:32:33.687
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT A CONTEST
BETWEEN AD CAMPAIGNS.

01:32:33.687 --> 01:32:36.689
- I'M TALKING ABOUT
SAVING YOUR SON.
- SO AM I.

01:32:38.691 --> 01:32:42.194
IT'S ABSOLUTE,
WHY I DID THIS, PANOS.

01:32:42.194 --> 01:32:46.198
FINALLY, IT'S JUST
ONE TRUE THING.

01:32:46.198 --> 01:32:48.702
ABSOLUTE.

01:32:48.702 --> 01:32:52.204
I DIDN'T ASK YOUR PERMISSION
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT IT.

01:32:53.205 --> 01:32:54.708
WE CAN'T AFFORD IT ANYMORE.

01:32:58.210 --> 01:33:00.212
OH, MY DEAR DOCTOR.

01:33:02.716 --> 01:33:05.217
YOU AND YOUR
GODDAMN ABSOLUTES.

01:33:05.217 --> 01:33:07.720
YOU'LL SEE WHAT
A SHALLOW, LITTLE THING
YOUR PRINCIPLES ARE...

01:33:07.720 --> 01:33:10.724
WHEN YOUR FAMILY'S
BLOWN TO HELL.

01:33:11.224 --> 01:33:13.726
AND YOU WON'T
BE ABLE TO TAKE BACK
ONE SINGLE WORD.

01:33:18.231 --> 01:33:20.232
JACOB. JACOB.
WHAT?

01:33:20.232 --> 01:33:23.235
COME ON, WAKE UP.
COME AND HEAR WHAT
YOUR MOTHER'S DONE.

01:33:23.235 --> 01:33:27.240
SHE'S DONE IT NOW, BOY.
SHE JUST COULDN'T KEEP
HER BIG MOUTH SHUT.

01:33:27.240 --> 01:33:29.742
DAD, STOP.
YOU'RE HURTING ME.
WHAT IS IT? WHAT'S WRONG?

01:33:29.742 --> 01:33:32.244
SHE'LL TELL YOU HERSELF.

01:33:32.244 --> 01:33:34.247
TELL HIM.
TELL HIM!

01:33:34.247 --> 01:33:38.250
WHAT KIND OF A LIFE
ARE WE GOING TO HAVE,
HMM?

01:33:39.251 --> 01:33:41.755
WHAT KIND OF A LIFE,
ALL OF US?

01:33:43.255 --> 01:33:47.259
I LOVE YOU AND I WANTED
TO SAVE YOU.

01:33:47.259 --> 01:33:50.262
BUT SAVE YOU FOR WHAT?
AS WHAT?

01:33:50.262 --> 01:33:53.265
EVERYTHING HE'S
BEEN FOR 16 YEARS,
EVERYTHING HE IS.

01:33:53.265 --> 01:33:56.269
- THAT WASN'T ENOUGH
TO MAKE HIM VALUABLE?
- OHH.

01:33:56.269 --> 01:33:58.771
YOU NEVER WANTED TO SAVE HIM.
YOU BROUGHT HIM
INTO THIS LIFE...

01:33:58.771 --> 01:34:01.273
- BUT YOU'RE NOT
WILLING TO FORGIVE HIM.
- I FORGIVE US ALL, BEN.

01:34:01.273 --> 01:34:03.276
JAKE, FOR GOD'S SAKE,
DON'T LISTEN TO HER.

01:34:03.777 --> 01:34:05.278
WE CAN'T GIVE UP NOW.
OH, LEAVE HIM ALONE.

01:34:05.778 --> 01:34:08.280
THERE'S STILL A CHANCE.
DON'T YOU HAVE ANY FAITH
IN HIM AT ALL?

01:34:08.280 --> 01:34:11.284
WE CAN STILL FIGHT THIS,
YOU AND ME TOGETHER.
YOU BACK OFF.

01:34:11.284 --> 01:34:14.787
BACK OFF MY SON.
IF HE'S YOUR SON,
THEN ACT LIKE IT.

01:34:14.787 --> 01:34:17.790
JACOB. JAKIE,
I DID THIS FOR YOU,
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

01:34:17.790 --> 01:34:20.293
I ONLY WAS TRYING TO HELP YOU.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?
OH, COME ON!

01:34:20.293 --> 01:34:23.796
YOU'RE ASKING A HELL OF A LOT
IF YOU EXPECT YOUR OWN SON TO
UNDERSTAND WHY YOU BETRAYED HIM.

01:34:23.796 --> 01:34:26.800
- I DIDN'T BE--
YOU CAN'T SAY THAT!
- GODDAMN IT, JUST STOP IT!

01:34:26.800 --> 01:34:28.801
ALL RIGHT?

01:34:32.805 --> 01:34:34.808
BOTH OF YOU.

01:34:44.767 --> 01:34:47.269
HEY, MOM! MOM!
WAKE UP!

01:34:47.269 --> 01:34:49.773
JACOB'S GONE.
HMM?

01:34:49.773 --> 01:34:51.774
WHAT?

01:34:56.278 --> 01:34:59.281
JACOB! HE'S GONE.
HE'S GONE.

01:35:03.786 --> 01:35:05.789
CHECK THE KITCHEN
AND THE BACK OF THE HOUSE.

01:35:06.289 --> 01:35:07.790
I ALREADY LOOKED.
LOOK AGAIN.

01:35:20.303 --> 01:35:22.304
OH, NO.

01:35:22.304 --> 01:35:24.306
OHH.

01:35:31.313 --> 01:35:34.316
THE JEEP'S GONE.
HE'S RUNNING AGAIN,
AND THIS TIME HE'LL NEVER STOP.

01:35:34.316 --> 01:35:37.820
NO, HE DIDN'T TAKE
ANY CLOTHES OR FOOD.
I'M ALMOST SURE, BEN.

01:35:37.820 --> 01:35:40.322
MAYBE HE DOESN'T THINK
HE'LL NEED THEM.

01:35:40.322 --> 01:35:44.327
MAYBE HE'S GONNA
DRIVE THAT THING
STRAIGHT INTO A TREE.

01:35:44.327 --> 01:35:47.329
OH, MY GOD.

01:35:47.329 --> 01:35:49.832
NO, THAT CAN'T BE TRUE.

01:36:00.843 --> 01:36:02.845
BEN? CAROLYN?

01:36:02.845 --> 01:36:05.849
I THINK YOU'D BETTER
COME WITH ME.

01:36:44.387 --> 01:36:46.388
DO THEY KNOW?
UH-UH.

01:36:50.893 --> 01:36:53.896
JACOB, WERE YOU RUNNING
TO SOME--

01:36:53.896 --> 01:36:57.399
NO, I CAME DOWN HERE
TO TELL 'EM THE TRUTH.
EVERYTHING.

01:36:57.399 --> 01:36:59.402
JUST LIKE I TOLD YOU.

01:37:01.403 --> 01:37:03.906
BUT YOU WON'T BELIEVE THIS.

01:37:03.906 --> 01:37:06.408
IT TURNS OUT
THAT IT'S NOT THAT EASY...

01:37:06.408 --> 01:37:08.411
EVEN IF YOU REALLY WANT TO.

01:37:08.411 --> 01:37:11.914
TURNS OUT THAT MY STATEMENT
ISN'T LEGAL UNLESS IT'S
SIGNED BY MY PARENTS.

01:37:14.918 --> 01:37:16.919
DAD?

01:37:18.921 --> 01:37:22.425
YOU WANT THIS NOW.
YOU THINK YOU WANT THIS,
BUT, JAKE,

01:37:22.425 --> 01:37:24.927
YOU'RE STILL UPSET
FROM LAST NIGHT.

01:37:24.927 --> 01:37:28.430
YOU'RE NOT
THINKING CLEARLY.
PLEASE, I AM. I AM.

01:37:28.430 --> 01:37:30.934
I AM THINKING CLEARLY.

01:37:30.934 --> 01:37:34.436
I'LL DO MY BEST TO LEAVE YOU
OUT OF THIS, BUT YOU MIGHT BE
IN SOME TROUBLE TOO.

01:37:34.436 --> 01:37:36.939
AND I'M SORRY.

01:37:36.939 --> 01:37:39.441
IS THAT WHAT YOU--

01:37:39.441 --> 01:37:43.445
OH, GOD, JAKE.
IS THAT WHAT YOU THINK
THIS WAS EVER ABOUT?

01:37:43.445 --> 01:37:45.448
FOR ONE MINUTE?

01:37:47.449 --> 01:37:49.451
I DON'T CARE
WHAT HAPPENS TO ME.

01:37:49.451 --> 01:37:51.954
WHY DO YOU THINK
I'VE BEEN DOING ALL THIS?

01:37:51.954 --> 01:37:55.958
YOU THINK I'M SOME--
SOME KIND OF A SELFISH BULLY?

01:37:55.958 --> 01:37:58.961
I'VE ALWAYS GOT TO HAVE
MY OWN WAY? JAKE.

01:38:00.462 --> 01:38:03.465
NO. DO YOU REMEMBER
WHAT YOU SAID TO ME?

01:38:04.466 --> 01:38:06.969
YOU SAID THE WORST THING
YOU CAN BE CALLED...

01:38:06.969 --> 01:38:10.472
IS SOMEONE WHO DIDN'T
STAND UP FOR HIS FAMILY.

01:38:12.474 --> 01:38:16.479
THIS IS MY WAY.
THIS IS HOW I'VE
GOTTA STAND UP.

01:38:17.980 --> 01:38:20.983
FOR US.
FOR OUR FAMILY.

01:38:26.989 --> 01:38:30.993
THEY'LL PROBABLY TAKE IT
WITH JUST MOM'S SIGNATURE
ON IT.

01:38:31.494 --> 01:38:33.495
BUT I NEED YOU TO DO THIS.

01:38:33.996 --> 01:38:36.498
I NEED YOU
TO DO THIS, PLEASE.

01:38:40.502 --> 01:38:42.504
I NEED THIS FOR ME,
PLEASE.

01:39:04.026 --> 01:39:06.528
I HAD TO BE STRONG.

01:39:08.530 --> 01:39:12.534
I HAD TO ACT CERTAIN
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT YOU
NEEDED FROM ME; ALL OF YOU.

01:39:19.041 --> 01:39:21.043
BUT I CAN'T DO THIS.

01:39:21.043 --> 01:39:23.045
[ Clipboard
Lands On Bench ]

01:39:27.549 --> 01:39:31.553
I CAN NEVER PUT MY HAND
TO ANYTHING THAT WOULD
TAKE YOU AWAY FROM ME.

01:39:32.054 --> 01:39:34.056
I LOVE YOU TOO MUCH, JAKE.

01:39:37.059 --> 01:39:40.062
NOTHING CAN EVER
TAKE ME AWAY FROM YOU.

01:39:44.066 --> 01:39:47.569
OH, SON. MY SON.

01:39:50.072 --> 01:39:52.074
[ Jacob Sobs ]

01:39:55.077 --> 01:39:57.579
I WISH WE COULD GO BACK.

01:39:57.579 --> 01:39:59.581
YEAH.

01:39:59.581 --> 01:40:02.084
I NEVER KNEW
HOW MUCH YOU LOVED ME.

01:40:07.589 --> 01:40:09.091
I NEVER KNEW THAT.

01:40:12.094 --> 01:40:15.097
[ Ben Sobs ]
[ Jacob ]
JUDITH?

01:40:16.598 --> 01:40:18.100
JAKE.

01:40:23.605 --> 01:40:25.607
[ Panos ]
LANGDALE'S A GOOD JUDGE.

01:40:25.607 --> 01:40:28.610
HE'S SMART AND HE'S FAIR,
AND I THINK I MAY HAVE
CONVINCED HIM...

01:40:28.610 --> 01:40:31.113
THAT PRISON TIME
IN THIS CASE WOULD BE
COMPLETELY INAPPROPRIATE.

01:40:31.113 --> 01:40:34.117
I THINK WE GOT
A REAL SHOT.

01:40:34.117 --> 01:40:36.618
BUT YOU SURE DIDN'T
LEAVE ME MUCH TO TRADE WITH.

01:40:37.119 --> 01:40:41.123
I GUESS WE HAVEN'T BEEN
THE MOST HELPFUL CLIENTS
YOU'VE EVER HAD.

01:40:41.123 --> 01:40:43.125
WHY DIDN'T YOU QUIT,
PANOS?

01:40:43.125 --> 01:40:46.128
I TOLD YOU
I'D DEFEND JACOB.

01:40:46.128 --> 01:40:49.132
OR MAYBE I JUST WANTED TO SEE
WHAT YOU TWO WOULD DO NEXT.

01:40:49.132 --> 01:40:51.633
[ Bailiff ]
HEAR YE, HEAR YE.

01:40:51.633 --> 01:40:54.636
THE THIRD DISTRICT COURT
IS NOW IN SESSION.

01:40:54.636 --> 01:40:57.639
THE HONORABLE HENRY LANGDALE
PRESIDING. ALL RISE.

01:40:59.641 --> 01:41:01.643
PLEASE BE SEATED.

01:41:05.147 --> 01:41:07.649
HAVING REVIEWED ALL THE
EVIDENCE AND TESTIMONY...

01:41:08.150 --> 01:41:11.153
IN THE CASE OF THE PEOPLE
VERSUS JACOB RYAN, JUVENILE,

01:41:11.153 --> 01:41:14.656
THIS COURT IS NOW PREPARED
TO RENDER JUDGMENT.

01:41:15.157 --> 01:41:17.659
MARTHA TAVERNER'S DEATH,
IN THE OPINION OF THIS COURT,

01:41:17.659 --> 01:41:21.163
WAS NEITHER PREMEDITATED
NOR DELIBERATELY CAUSED
BY THE DEFENDANT.

01:41:21.163 --> 01:41:24.166
[ Spectators Murmuring ]

01:41:24.166 --> 01:41:28.670
THERE WAS A HEATED ARGUMENT,
A MUTUALLY RECKLESS STRUGGLE,
BUT NO CRIMINAL INTENT.

01:41:28.670 --> 01:41:32.174
[ Murmuring Continues ]

01:41:34.176 --> 01:41:38.680
YOUNG MAN,
I'M ALSO MINDFUL THAT YOU'VE
EXPRESSED DEEP REMORSE;

01:41:38.680 --> 01:41:40.682
THAT YOU'VE MADE A FULL
AND FREE CONFESSION...

01:41:40.682 --> 01:41:45.687
AND DONE SO AT YOUR OWN
INSISTENCE WITHOUT STIPULATING
A PLEA BARGAIN.

01:41:47.189 --> 01:41:51.193
NEVERTHELESS, YOU HAVE
A CLEAR CULPABILITY.

01:41:51.693 --> 01:41:54.696
BY RUNNING AWAY,
BY COVERING UP
YOUR INVOLVEMENT...

01:41:54.696 --> 01:41:56.698
IN THE DEATH
OF MARTHA TAVERNER,

01:41:56.698 --> 01:41:59.701
YOU CAST GRAVE DOUBTS
ON YOUR OWN ACTIONS...

01:42:00.202 --> 01:42:04.206
AND YOU SHORT-CIRCUITED
THE VERY PROTECTIONS
AFFORDED YOU UNDER THE LAW.

01:42:07.209 --> 01:42:09.211
JACOB RYAN, PLEASE RISE.

01:42:14.216 --> 01:42:16.218
- I FIND YOU GUILTY...
- [ Crowd Gasps, Murmurs ]

01:42:16.218 --> 01:42:20.722
OF INVOLUNTARY MANSLAUGHTER
IN THE SECOND DEGREE.

01:42:20.722 --> 01:42:23.725
I SENTENCE YOU TO BE TAKEN
FROM THIS PLACE AND CONFINED...

01:42:24.226 --> 01:42:26.728
AT THE JUVENILE CORRECTION
FACILITY AT FRAMINGHAM...

01:42:26.728 --> 01:42:29.731
FOR A PERIOD
NOT TO EXCEED FIVE YEARS.

01:42:29.731 --> 01:42:33.235
[ Spectators Murmuring ]
[ Gavel Bangs ]

01:42:53.255 --> 01:42:55.757
STILL THINK
IT WAS WORTH IT?

01:43:05.934 --> 01:43:10.939
[ Judith Narrating ]
MY FATHER HAD TO SERVE ALMOST
A YEAR FOR DESTROYING EVIDENCE.

01:43:10.939 --> 01:43:15.444
JACOB WAS RELEASED ON PROBATION
AFTER TWO YEARS.

01:43:15.444 --> 01:43:18.447
HE HAS TO GO TO COUNSELING,
THOUGH.

01:43:20.449 --> 01:43:22.951
SO WE HAVE THEM BACK.

01:43:22.951 --> 01:43:24.953
BUT NONE OF US IS FREE.

01:43:24.953 --> 01:43:27.956
EACH OF US
IS MARKED FOREVER NOW.

01:43:27.956 --> 01:43:30.959
BEFORE... AND AFTER.

01:43:32.461 --> 01:43:34.463
I LOOK AT JACOB NOW...

01:43:34.463 --> 01:43:37.466
AND I THINK ABOUT
HOW DIFFERENT OUR LIVES
MIGHT HAVE BEEN.

01:43:37.466 --> 01:43:41.470
ALL OF US. AND THAT'S
THE SADDEST PART OF ALL.

01:43:41.970 --> 01:43:43.972
[ Jacob ]
HEY, JUDE, LOOK!

01:43:47.476 --> 01:43:49.978
[ Judith ]
BUT LATELY, SOMETIMES,

01:43:49.978 --> 01:43:53.482
I CAN FEEL MYSELF STARTING
TO COME ALIVE AGAIN.

01:43:53.482 --> 01:43:55.484
AND IT'S SCARY, KIND OF.

01:43:55.984 --> 01:43:57.986
I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT'S EVEN ALLOWED.

01:43:59.988 --> 01:44:04.993
MAYBE YOU CAN'T EXPECT
TO KEEP HAPPINESS OUT
OF YOUR LIFE FOREVER,

01:44:04.993 --> 01:44:07.996
ANY MORE THAN TROUBLE.

01:44:07.996 --> 01:44:12.000
YOUR WHOLE LIFE CAN CHANGE
IN A SECOND,

01:44:12.000 --> 01:44:14.503
AND YOU NEVER EVEN KNOW
WHEN IT'S COMING.

